title: slaw
directions: Pour enough very hot water almost boiling plus 1 heaping tablespoonful salt over the first 4 ingredients, cover and let set for 1 hour; drain well.
Mix the remaining ingredients while mixture is setting.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish sprayed with vegetable spray. Bring broth and soup to boil and pour over chicken.

A can of drained mixed vegetables or cooked and drained fresh vegetables can be added at this time. Make a batter out of remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. This is my Mammaw Oakes' recipe.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook slowly until sugar, syrup and water spins about a 7-inch thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook until smell parched.
Remove from heat and add salt and soda.
Mix quickly and spread on greased surface.

title: baby carrot juice
directions: Blend together and serve.

title: never fail refrigerator rolls
directions: Measure 6 cups of sifted flour.
Combine milk, sugar and shortening in saucepan; scald, but do not boil.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast cakes and let stand 5 to 10 minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Add salt.
Gradually beat in the sifted flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead gently until smooth.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until double in size.

title: baked beans
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish (200°), or crock-pot; without soaking.
Turn crock-pot on low and cook 10 hours depending on beans.
Test for doneness.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jeannine's chicken
directions: Mix soup, onion, wine, mushrooms with liquid and lemon juice. Pour chicken pieces in baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 1 egg at a time, then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let cake cool before taking out of pan.

title: black walnut buttermilk cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, cooking oil, flour, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Have oleo at room temperature.
Cream together oleo and milk. Add sugar slowly and mix well.
Add pecans and coconut and mix well.
With hands, roll into balls and put into refrigerator; let cool.
Melt Gulfwax in top of double boiler.
Add chocolate chips and melt.
Using toothpicks, dip balls of candy in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.
Let candy set.
Makes about 140 balls.

title: caddo lake cole slaw
directions: Mix all of this together and refrigerate.
Make several hours or the evening before you need it.
The longer you keep it the better.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Separate biscuits on a cookie sheet.
Flatten them firmly.
Spoon on sauce.
Add cheese and toppings and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a quick snack.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: *Tomato paste makes thicker sauce.

title: noodles-n-beef
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Meanwhile, prepare remainder.
Brown meat and drain. In a separate saucepan, melt margarine, then add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and thicken.
Mix noodles, beef and sauce.
Top with cheese.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and place into the bottom of a greased 9x13-inch pan.
Layer cheese and bacon.
Mix together milk, eggs and pour over the top.

title: texas bar-b-q brisket
directions: Rub brisket with unseasoned tenderizing salt.
Place in pan fat side up.
Stir together liquid smoke, worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, pepper and pour over meat.
Cover tightly with foil. Cook in oven 300 degrees for 1 hour; turn down to 200 degrees and cook 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 10 to 12 persons.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil until brown.
Remove from skillet. Add onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, cinnamon, cumin and 1/8 teaspoon black pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Drain excess fat from the skillet.

title: russian tea mix
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in tightly covered container.
For each serving, place 2 rounded tablespoonfuls of mix in cup; fill with 1 cup of boiling water and stir well.
Yields 6 cups mix, 32 (1-cup) servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saut pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and stock.	Cook until smooth.
Add pimiento and soup.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Drain.
Add sauce and cooked chicken.	Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 250 degrees to 300 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to shortening mixture, mixing well.
Blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Leave in pan.

title: country club squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in 1/2 cup boiling water until tender; drain and mash.
Combine squash mixture, sour cream, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, butter and paprika.
Sprinkle over squash mixture.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes and bananas
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Place the potatoes in an 8 or 9-inch baking dish and place the bananas over them.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Pour the pineapple juice over the mixture and dot with the margarine.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: citrus trifle
directions: About 3 hours before serving or early in the day:

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover in saucepan; drain.
Chop chicken.
Combine with onion and cream cheese in bowl.
Mix milk, soup and salsa in small bowl.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until squash is tender and mash. Add the last 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray eight 6-ounce brioche pans (or jumbo muffin pan cups 3 x 1 1/2 inches) with nonstick cooking spray.
Place the prepared brioche pan or muffin pan in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan for easier handling.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix together beans and pepper, then add sauce made of remainder of ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot several hours.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of water.
Add fruit mix.
Pour in a bowl and refrigerate.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Can easily be made low-fat by using lite sour cream and lite cream of chicken soup.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, using a vegetable brush; drain on rack.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices; discard ends.
Add onions, garlic and salt.
Mix thoroughly; cover with crushed ice or cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly; remove garlic cloves.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bring to a hard boil, no more than 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes before serving.

title: double cherry chiffon pie
directions: In medium saucepan stir together gelatin and water.
With whisk beat in egg yolks.
Cook over low hear stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved and mixture begins to thicken (approx. 5-8 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in pie filling.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly (approx. 1 hour).
In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed until foamy.
Add sugar 1 Tbsp. at a time; beating constantly until sugar is dissolved* and whites form soft peaks. Gently fold in cherry mixture.
Pile mixture into pie shell and chill about 3 hours until firm.

title: parmesan pepper bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast, 1 1/2 teaspoons pepper and salt.
Gradually stir hot water into dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
With spoon, stir in cheese and enough additional flour to make soft dough.

title: potato chip salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and vinegar. Mix well. Add all other ingredients except chips. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add potato chips.
Toss lightly.
Serves 6.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water, cinnamon and cloves to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add tea bags.
Cover; let sit for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Add sugar, orange juice, lemonade and 4 cups cold water.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes; put on to boil.
Brown ground beef; cook onions, if desired.
Drain and put beef in bottom of casserole dish (1 1/2-quart to 2 1/2-quart size).

title: easy beef stew
directions: Cut meat into
bite-size chunks, then cover with flour. In Dutch oven, heat oil.
Brown
meat on both sides and reduce heat to	medium.
Add
onion,
garlic
and
remaining
flour. Gradually add water,	bouillon cubes, salt, Worcestershire and pepper.
Cook stirring until mixture is slightly thick.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2
hours,
then
add potatoes, carrots and peas.	Cook 30 minutes longer.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
In large bowl, toss apple slices with cinnamon, nutmeg, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup flour. Spoon apple filling into 13 x 9-inch ceramic or glass baking dish.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to mixture.
Place flour in large bowl.
Add dates, orange slices and nuts.
Stir to coat each piece.
Add this mixture with coconut to creamed mixture.
This makes very stiff dough.
Mix with hands. Put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours. Combine orange juice and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake while hot. Let stand in pan overnight.
Cake keeps well.
Better after a few days.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat vigorously until well beaten. Spread mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 16 brownies. Exchange:
One brownie equals 1 1/2 bread and 1 1/2 fat.
One brownie contains 136 calories.

title: chocolate-dipped shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine flour, butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup of miniature chocolate chips and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets coated with nonstick finish.
Shape into 2-inch logs.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden around edges.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: plum jam
directions: Combine plums, water, lemon juice and pectin in a large sauce pot.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat, stirring frequently. Add sugar; return to a rolling boil.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield: about 8 half pints.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Spread bread cubes in bottom of greased 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Blend eggs, milk, pepper, salt, mustard and onion.
Pour over bread and cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° until egg mixture is set (40 to 45 minutes).
Sprinkle bacon bits over casserole last 10 minutes or baking.
Serves 10.

title: crab and avocado enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion, chopped olives and mushrooms in butter.
Remove from heat and stir in crabmeat and mashed avocado, mixed with 1 cup sour cream, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Dip each tortilla in hot oil and drain on absorbent paper.
Fill each tortilla with some of crab mixture, roll and place seam side down in buttered 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Cover with remaining sour cream and sprinkle with cheese and sliced olives.
Bake for 20 minutes and serve immediately, topped with fresh avocado slices.
This dish does not hold for any length of time.
The moisture from seafood makes tortillas crack.

title: red fish delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except mustard and red fish and mix well.
Spread mustard all over fish.
Let set 10 minutes. Coat fish in batter mix.
Deep fry fish.

title: pam luna's mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone the chicken.
Combine the soups, broth, pimentos, Cheez Whiz, onion, chili powder, green chilies and jalapeno pepper in a large saucepan.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1/2 bag of tortilla chips.
Add the deboned chicken to the saucepan and pour this mixture over the chips.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy fruit-filled layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour
two 8 x 1 1/2 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake as directed on package.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: This is a nice moist cake and easy to prepare.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Spread cream cheese, blended with sufficient cream to soften it) over bottom of cooled, baked pie shell.
Wash berries, hull them and drain well. Place half the berries (the choicest ones) in the cheese coated pie shell.
Mash and strain remaining berries until
juice is well extracted. Bring juice to boiling point and slowly stir in sugar and cornstarch which have been mixed together.
Cook slowly for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool and spread over uncooked berries in pie shell. Place pie in refrigerator until very cold.
Decorate with Cool Whip just before serving and top with strawberries.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter; mix in vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and press into glass container (11 x 15-inch).
Melt Hershey bars and pour on top.

title: sauteed cabbage
directions: In frypan, melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Mix, cover and cook for about 10 minutes until cabbage is tender.

title: algerian sweet meat
directions: *Order ahead from butcher if you use lamb.

title: dilly bread(for auto bread baker)
directions: In order listed, place yeast, soda, bread flour and salt and egg in inner pan.
Warm remaining ingredients.
Add them.
Select white bread and push "Start."
Lightly brush the top with melted butter at baking time if you wish.

title: brandy ice
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve as a milk shake.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Add onion and cook until tender, stirring frequently. Stir in remaining ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook for about 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cheesy brunch pie
directions: In medium bowl, whisk together eggs and sour cream until blended.
Stir in bacon, cheese and parsley.
Pour into frozen crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° on preheated baking sheet 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: quick and easy barbecue meatballs
directions: Note:
For best results, use lean hamburger (ground meat).

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, butter and cake mix.
Press into long cake pan.
On top of cake pour powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs (cream all three with mixer and pour on top of cake).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: baked ham
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Slice ham in large slices.
Cover ham with lots of mustard; put ham in iron pot.
Almost cover ham with milk.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In small bowl, combine melted butter and crushed Ritz. Set aside cracker mixture and almonds. In large bowl, combine all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Cover with cracker mixture. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated roast
directions: Combine all ingredients, except roast.
Place roast in bag in a shallow pan.
Pour
marinade over roast; cover for 24 hours in refrigerator, turning once.
Bake in marinade at 350° for 2 or 3 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, lemon juice, apples and walnuts.
Let congeal slightly.
Pour into mold. Chill until firm.
May garnish with mayonnaise if you wish. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy muffins
directions: Mix ingredients until pasty.
Grease muffin tins; fill 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Saute bacon, onion and pepper until lightly browned.
Pour undrained lima beans and tomatoes in greased casserole dish. Add the beans and bacon mixture and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: della's cabbage slaw
directions: When mixture boils, pour over the cabbage while still hot. Cover and let stand for 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Stir and serve.
Keeps well for several days.

title: stay-a-bed stew
directions: Place beef, vegetables and bay leaf in a dish with tight-fitting lid.
Pour soup and water over top.
Cover dish with lid and cook 4 1/2 to 5 hours at 250°.

title: chocolate chews
directions: * I use low-calorie milk instead.
See recipe for Sweetened Condensed (low calorie) milk.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix together and put into greased pan (7 x 11). Bake at 375 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl in order given.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to lukewarm mixture.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough, approximately 5 to 5 1/2 cups flour. Attach dough hook.
Add first 2 cups, then one at a time, then 1/2 cup.
Follow directions on mixer. Run 10 minutes after putting mixer on lock.
Grease bowl and let rise.
When dough pulls away from sides of bowl, put into 2 greased loaf pans and let rise again. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
For rolls, bake 25 to 30 minutes. Will sound hollow when baked.

title: georgia's chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in uncooked pie crust.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until pie is firm and will not shake.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and syrup together; bring to a boil in microwave.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix with oatmeal and pat into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter and spread on top.
Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken
directions: Prepare chicken.
Wash, skin and cut into serving pieces. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Dissolve bouillon in water. Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour over bouillon and water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove cover and bake until slightly browned.

title: good and easy pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
With mixer cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt (don't omit this step).
Add flour and yogurt (with lemon juice) alternately to sugar-butter mixture.
Add flavorings.
Fold egg whites into batter very gently.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until toothpick comes out clean. Let cool and invert onto cake plate.
You may glaze, but I do not.

title: garbanzo and black olive salad
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, mix all ingredients together in a medium-sized bowl.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes and pour Eagle Brand milk over hot cake.
Crumble Butterfingers and sprinkle over top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: fruited marshmallow salad
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, flour, salt, lemon juice and juice from oranges and pineapple.
Cook until thickens.
Cool.
Add marshmallows, oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: chili upside down pie
directions: Prepare cornbread mix in tiara pan according to directions on package.
Brown beef and onion together; add beans and taco seasoning and enough water to combine all ingredients.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Unmold cornbread, spread chili mix in center. Cover with Cheddar cheese and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve like pie slices, topping with sour cream, lettuce, tomatoes, picante sauce, etc.

title: microwave chocolate pudding
directions: In a 2-quart microproof dish, stir together milk and cornstarch until dissolved.
Stir in sugar and sugar substitute, cocoa and salt.
Cook at 100% power (High), stir several times, for 6 minutes, until thickened.
Stir in the margarine and vanilla. Pour into individual servings, cover and refrigerate. Makes five 1/2-cup servings.

title: pecan raisin muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in pecans and raisins. Beat egg and milk together and add to dry mixture.
Stir lightly. Fill 12 greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cereal and apricots.
Blend milk, egg and oil.
Add flour mixture, stirring until moistened.
Pour into greased pans, 9 x 5-inch and bake at 350° for 1 hour; 2 smaller pans about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail caramel frosting
directions: Combine butter, sugar and whipping cream in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Yield: Enough for one 3 layer cake.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix dry mustard and water and let set 10 minutes.
Add mustard mixture to remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: doris' bean salad
directions: Drain and mix the first 6 ingredients. Combine sugar, vinegar, vegetable oil, salt and pepper for a dressing.
Pour dressing over vegetables and marinate for several hours.
Keeps well for several days.

title: date nut bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture with orange juice.
Blend well. Fold in dates and walnuts.
Pour into two greased, floured and waxed paper lined 8 x 4 x 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for 45-50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Season with salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomato soup and tomato sauce to meat mixture.
Cook for 15 minutes.
In the meantime, cook elbow macaroni separately.
When meat and macaroni are cooked, mix them all together in a baking dish and stir in Cheddar cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cream with mixer and pour over crust. Dice about 4-5 bananas and put on top.
Put 1 can of drained crushed pineapple on top.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peachy pork picante over rice
directions: Coat pork with taco seasoning mix; brown in oil.
Add salsa and peach jelly.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry truffle
directions: Make pudding following directions on box.
Whip the cream until firm.
Slice pound cake and spread preserves on each side of slice.
Layer pound cake in a 3-quart glass bowl on bottom, then along sides (punch bowl works well).
Layer strawberries, pudding, whipped cream and pound cake.
Repeat layers. Top with whipped cream and chopped nuts.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and place in a mixing bowl. Drizzle with lemon juice. Add onion, celery, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Toss lightly to mix. Cover and chill for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: You will need one large bowl for this recipe.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Combine water and sugar. Bring just to a boil. Pour over the juices and zest, stir in spearmint leaves. Steep one hour; strain. To serve, combine 2 tablespoons of the syrup with 2/3 c. of ice and water.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in small amount of salted water in saucepan for 5 minutes; drain.
Add soup, sour cream and carrots; mix well.
Mix stuffing mix and margarine in bowl.
Layer half the stuffing mixture, zucchini mixture and remaining stuffing mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: best bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl stir together bran cereal, brown sugar, flour, baking powder and soda.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Boil fryers with a little water.
Add poultry seasoning.
Cook until tender.
Reserve broth.
Cook rice in broth, using 2 1/2 cups broth and water, if necessary.
Saute onions, green peppers and celery.
Combine cooked rice, sauteed onions, green peppers and celery, tomatoes, deboned chicken and cheese.
Mix with drained peas.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake a few minutes until cheese is well blended.

title: poor man's delight
directions: Fry hamburger with onion, carrot, celery and green pepper. Make sure that you keep stirring the mixture so it doesn't burn or get too hard.
Add tomatoes and let simmer about 20 minutes. Using mashed potato mix, follow directions for making mashed potatoes, however, use 1/3 less milk or water.
Pour hamburger and veggies into a buttered baking dish and spoon the mashed potatoes over the top, keeping it evenly spread.
Put under broiler for about 3 minutes or until potatoes brown a little. Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut in pieces.
Add soups, mushrooms, chopped water chestnuts and 3/4 can of noodles.
Mix.
Reserve rest of noodles for topping. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Casserole can be made in advance by omitting noodles. Add noodles before baking.

title: 9-inch custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs slightly, then beat in rest of ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes more or until a silver knife inserted 1-inch from side of pan into filling comes out clean.
The center may still look a bit soft, but will set later.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour four 1-pound coffee cans.
Mix dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Mix wet ingredients in another bowl and combine until smooth.
Add nuts and bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven candied sweet potatoes
directions: Layer half each of the potatoes, brown sugar, butter and salt. Repeat.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until glazed.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until lightly browned.

title: breakfast sausage dish
directions: Fix 1 day before serving.
Fry, crumble and drain sausage or bacon.
Beat eggs.
Take crust off bread and cube.
Cube cheese and mix well.
Pour in 9x9 inch pan and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Boil first 3 things for 2 minutes; cool.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir until right consistency for spreading.
Great on top of pumpkin cookies.

title: spinach delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: mystery pie
directions: Slice bananas.
Put in bottom of 2 graham crusts.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour on top of bananas.
Chill.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Bone and cube chicken.
Add celery, green grapes, salt and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
Just prior to serving, add the toasted almonds and mix well.
Save a few for garnish on the top.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Separate crackers and put on cookie sheet.
Boil sugars, butter and margarine together for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over the graham crackers.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove immediately onto wax paper and cool.

title: apple and pear salad
directions: In small bowl, combine sour cream and lemon juice.
With fork, break Roquefort cheese into 1-inch pieces.
Fold pieces of cheese into sour cream mixture.
Cover and chill until ready to serve. With sharp knife, core and thinly slice apples and pears.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place casserole uncovered in pan with 1-inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 90 minutes.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and set aside.
In large bowl mix eggs, oil, and vanilla.
Beat for 1 minute.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with apple mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake 45 - 50 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: roach control
directions: Mix shortening and sugar until creamy.
Combine flour, onion and boric acid.
Add to shortening mixture; blend well.
Add a little water to soften the dough.
Form into small balls.
Place balls throughout the house.
Store in plastic bag.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt and set aside.
Beat together eggs and banana mixture and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour and egg mixture alternately to shortening and sugar.
Mix well and fold in nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans and bake for about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: halupki
directions: Cut out core from cabbage and scald.
Cut each leaf separately and scald only until limp.
Saute chopped onions in shortening. Wash rice, drain and leave about 1/2 cup water in rice.
Add to rice the ground meat, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic powder (just a shake of each) and sauteed onion.
Mix well.
Cut off the thick part of the cabbage leaf.
Fill each leaf with enough ground meat filling so that you can roll and tuck in ends.
Cut up small pieces of cabbage which you can't use and spread on bottom of pot. Layer the halupki.
Mix tomato soup and paste in some water. Pour over halupki.
Fill pot to at least 2 inches above.
Squeeze over sauerkraut and lay on top.
Cook for at least 2 hours or until rice is cooked.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix gelatin, hot water and strawberries (slightly thawed). Set aside to congeal slightly.
Combine cream cheese, whipped topping, walnuts and powdered sugar.
Pour into crusts.
After strawberry mixture has slightly thickened, carefully spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: herb jelly
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, water, vinegar, herb and color.
Bring to boil.
Stir in pectin.
Heat to full boil and boil hard for 1 minute.
Strain into clean hot jelly glasses.
Cover with 1/8 inch hot paraffin.
Makes seven 1/2 pints.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine the soups and Veg-All.
Mix and heat the remaining ingredients until margarine is melted.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pepper to taste.
Mix and place over soup and vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and put into 11 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put butter, flour, milk, pepper, salt and sugar in macaroni and mix thoroughly.
Grate Cheddar over top of macaroni and put into oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot german beans
directions: Drain beans and save 1/2 cup liquid.
Cook bacon until crisp; remove bacon pieces.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup liquid from beans.
Heat slowly to blend flavors.

title: beef stew
directions: Put pieces of beef into stew pot with dab of butter to brown. When browned, cover with the wine or cider.
Add to taste the spices and salt. Allow to boil 2 hours.
Add, in bite size pieces, vegetables on hand. Add liquid to keep covered and continue cooking until vegetables are cooked.
Add a 2 tablespoon size ball of butter rolled in flour and stir until thickened. Serve with chunks of bread.

title: hearty meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine catsup, sugar and mustard; set aside.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients and 1/3 cup sauce mixture.
Mix well.
In large shallow baking dish, shape into loaf.
Bake for 1 hour; remove from oven.
Pour remaining sauce over loaf; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes until can break apart.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and golden brown on top.

title: lobster newburg
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and salt. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir about half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg.
Return all to pan.
Cook and stir mixture until thickened, but do not boil.
Stir lobster, dry sherry, ground red pepper and white or black pepper.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: family meat loaf(diabetic)
directions: Sprinkle meat with dry milk thoroughly.
Add other items, mixing well.
Will be sticky.
Lightly grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomatoes and eggs.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, egg and milk.
Sift together and add dry ingredients.
Mix in pecans and fruit.
Chill overnight.
Drop by teaspoon about 2-inches apart on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done. Spread chicken on bottom of casserole dish. Mix celery and mushroom soup with sour cream and pour over chicken. Put in oven until it starts to bubble up. Remove from oven and crumble crackers and put on top. Return to oven until the crackers are brown.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine remaining ingredients
in a large bowl. Add yeast mixture;
stir
until
moist dough is formed. Allow to rise (about 1 hour
in
warm
place) until doubled. Put 1/2 cup flour on clean
surface
and
knead dough. Put
into
a large oiled casserole.
Let
rise
until doubled, approximately 1/2 hour. Bake at 350° for
to
50 minutes. While hot, brush with melted
butter
and
sprinkle with salt. Serve warm.

title: chicken crepe
directions: Melt butter; add onion or shallot and saute until soft.
Add flour; cook until bubbly.
Add half and half; cook until thick and smooth.
Add chicken and sherry to half of the sauce.

title: tortilla melts
directions: Grill chicken breasts until done.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cut into slender strips.
Fry flour tortillas in hot oil until lightly brown, turning once.
Spread each tortilla with approximately 2 tablespoons chunky salsa.
Layer each with chicken strips and Mozzarella cheese.
Place on baking sheet or plate and place in preheated oven or microwave until cheese melts.
May top with lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mrs. r's pancakes
directions: Do not overbeat when mixing ingredients. Do not put any grease in skillet or batter.

title: red cabbage relish
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a very large bowl.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in a saucepan.
Pour over cabbage mixture in bowl.
Chill overnight.
Several days is even better.

title: onion butter bread
directions: Soften (do not melt) butter and mix with soup mix.
Spread on slices of Italian bread and bake in foil, open at top, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick homemade caramel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Defrost dough in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove and slice into 10 pieces, then cut those in half. Melt some of the butter and pour into a round cake pan.
Grease sides.
Pour half of pudding in bottom.
Set the rest aside for later.
Add cinnamon and nuts to pudding and butter layers. Place sliced dough in pan evenly.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 4 or one big husband.

title: cream of wheat cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl; add egg and beat well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Must refrigerate 24 hours. Good with raw veggies, cocktail rye and Wheat Thins.

title: parsley rice ring
directions: Combine rice and parsley.
Pack into an ungreased 5 1/2-cup ring mold.
Turn out at once on warm platter.
Serve with Shrimp Creole.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook meat until brown; stir in taco mix.
Let cool.
Place lettuce, tomatoes, onions, beans, olives and cheese in a bowl. Add cooled meat and crushed bag of chips.
Mix Imo and Uncle Dan's mix in blender.
Add to salad and blend together.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Whip the whipping cream until fluffy and smooth.
Blend with sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Fold in pineapple, cherries and bananas.
Freeze overnight in muffin tins lined with paper liners or a glass 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut into individual servings and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: easy oven baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate slices, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine the next 5 ingredients; drizzle over potato and onion slices.
Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, for an additional 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: philadelphia butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix syrup, milk and sugar in double boiler until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Beat for 30 minutes or until thick.
Serve over ice cream or pound cake. Makes 2 cups.

title: fried chitlins
directions: Coat the chitlins in the flour and pepper mixed together. Place them in the oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Cook slowly, about 10 minutes on each side, turning until crispy and brown all over.
Drain on paper towels.

title: bread sticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil, salt and beaten egg. Add 3 cups flour.
Make a well with rest of flour and add yeast mixture.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Add more flour, if needed.
Let rise until double in bulk and punch down.
Pinch off pieces and roll about the size of your finger.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 325° until brown.
Do not let rise again. Sprinkle with garlic salt and oil after baked.

title: fruit cup
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream on medium speed until well blended.
Serve with assorted fruits (apples, grapes, strawberries, etc.).

title: mock potato salad
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender.
Add sliced eggs, mayo, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir gently and serve.

title: california casserole
directions: Brown meat in batches in a large, heavy frying pan.
(Don't put too much meat into the pan at once; it will cause the meat to turn grey instead of brown.)
Saute garlic and onion with last batch of meat.
Return all meat to pan.
Sprinkle chili powder over meat; mix well.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, half the olives and all the diced chiles.
Simmer over very low heat for 15 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub and pierce potatoes.
Bake on cookie sheet for 45 minutes and cool briefly.
Halve lengthwise; remove flesh leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Raise heat to 500°.
Combine butter and soy sauce.
Brush both sides of shell with butter mixture.
Place on cookie sheet with outside up and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: beth's poor boys
directions: Mix Italian
dressing
together as directed on package. Set aside.
Cut chuck
roast into chunks; cut off fat and take out bone.
Add	meat,
dressing and remaining ingredients in a crock-pot.	Cook on
low
all
day.
Pull meat into shreds, if desired.
Serve on buns.
This
is really good with a slice of Cheddar cheese.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Scald milk. Sift in corn meal and cook until thickened. Add salt, sugar, shortening and beaten egg yolks. Blend thoroughly and add baking powder. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Turn into greased baking dish and bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with a spoon from dish in which bread was baked. Serves 6.

title: shrimp in wok(light recipe)
directions: Peel shrimp.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add cornstarch and pepper.
Stir in lemon juice and soy sauce.
Stir and set aside.
Heat wok to high.
Add oil; add green onions and green pepper.
Stir-fry.
Remove.
Add shrimp.
Stir-fry 2 to 4 minutes until done.
Stir in lemon juice mixture.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add green onions and peppers.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: banana cake
directions: Add baking soda to sour cream; set aside until needed.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat one at a time.
Add sour cream-baking soda mixture.
Add bananas, then flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla last.
Bake at 350° in a greased Bundt pan, sprinkled with flour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry-pecan bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl. Add pecans and mix.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into dry ingredients. Stir enough to dampen all ingredients and pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well; chill and serve with various raw vegetables.

title: vegetables
directions: In a heavy skillet or wok, heat sesame oil.
Quickly saute green beans and asparagus until skins wrinkle.
Add sherry, soy sauce and chicken stock and simmer until tender.
Toss with toasted sesame seed.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Combine in a large bowl.
Place noodles in a large lasagna pan and spread 1/2 the cottage cheese mix over, 1/2 the meat mixture. Put 1/2 a 1 pound bag Mozzarella cheese over this.
Then repeat with noodles, cottage cheese, meat and don't put the rest of the Mozzarella on top until done, then melt.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs 1 at a time. Blending flour and whipping cream, add salt and flavoring. Start with cold oven; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: natilla(cuban custard)
directions: Place milk and salt in a large pan over medium heat.
In a separate bowl, thoroughly mix the sugar and egg yolks and add to the milk.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to milk, sugar and egg mixture.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Take off stove and stir in vanilla.
Pour in 1 large or 10 small bowls.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered cinnamon. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix with a mixer the sweet potatoes, 1/3 cup margarine, eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, water and oil together until smooth.
Add cake mix and dry pudding.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour mixture into a well buttered Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Sift confectioners sugar on top.

title: cube steak italian style
directions: Slice steak into strips.
Saute with onion and green pepper (if desired) in oil.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, salt and pepper. Cover; simmer 10 minutes or longer, if desired.
Serve over pasta of your choice or rice.

title: caramel apple bars
directions: Make sugar cookie mixes as directed on box.
Spread on an ungreased large cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to apple pie filling, if desired.
Crush apples with a potato masher, if desired.
Remove cookie crust from oven. Spread apples on top.
Heat up caramel until it can be dribbled over the top of the apples.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apple pie filling in a cake pan. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbs form.
Sprinkle crumbs over apples and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Serve over green tossed salad.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: mrs. boyd's cream cheese kiffles
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add flour.
Form 50 balls from dough.
Chill.
Roll into triangles on powdered sugar.
Fill with small amount (about 1/2 teaspoon) pastry filling.
Roll up triangle, sealing in filling.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
When cool, dust with additional powdered sugar.

title: mystery salad
directions: Add all together and chill.

title: french-fried onions
directions: Batter:
Combine in sifter the sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Add oil; stir in milk; amount depends upon thinness of coating desired.
Slice onions approximately 1/4 inch thick.
Heat oil.
Dip only a few rings at a time in hot oil; cook until golden brown.
Rings may be kept warm on a cookie sheet in low heated oven.

title: mercers chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Cook marshmallows, milk, cocoa and pinch of salt in double boiler until marshmallows dissolve. Cool. Add vanilla, lemon juice or rum or orange juice or 1 tablespoon of any juice you prefer. Fold in Cool Whip or whipped cream. Pour in a baked pie shell and chill. Cover with Cool Whip or whipped cream and top with pecans.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Chop basil leaves, stem spinach and mince garlic.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini and bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Mix 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese into soup.
Simmer until tortellini are just about tender.
Add tomatoes, spinach and basil.
Simmer 2 more minutes.
Serve, passing additional Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: batter for fried shrimp
directions: Dip shrimp in mixture and fry. Can "dribble" mixture into oil and it will make "chips."

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo.
In mixing bowl, put butter, rice, celery, onion, soup and water.
Stir to blend.
Add broccoli and cheese slices.
Stir well.
Place in casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 40 minutes, uncovered.
Remove from oven and spread prepared stuffing mix evenly on top.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dissolve cubes in hot water.
Add to cream cheese and garlic powder.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Serve with celery sticks, carrot sticks, cucumbers, green pepper, radishes, fresh broccoli and cauliflower.

title: flan (custard)
directions: In a small skillet, heat and stir the 1/3 cup of sugar over medium heat, until sugar melts and becomes golden brown.
Quickly pour caramelized sugar into a 3-cup ring mold, tilting to coat bottom and sides.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk, the 1/4 cup of sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour into caramelized coated mold.

title: cottage cheese cake or kuchen
directions: Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Is good on ribs, chicken or pork chops.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Add water to raisins and sugar.
Boil until even with raisins and raisins are done.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Make a well of flour, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
In center, add beaten eggs, yeast mixture and milk.
Gradually incorporate dry into wet ingredients until dough forms.
Knead in the margarine.
Knead well in bowl. Cover and let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Punch down gently.
Cut into 12 pieces.
Arrange in well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in broth and cream.
Let boil until it thickens.
Add chicken, peas and carrots.
Stir well.
Pour in shallow casserole dish.
Bake until hot through.
Top with paprika pastry.
Bake at 425° until pastry is brown.
Serve hot from the oven.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine and beat with eggs and sugar.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine and stir with crushed graham crackers.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Spread margarine, sugar and egg mixture on crust.
Spread pineapple on for next layer.
Split bananas lengthwise and dredge in pineapple juice for the next layer. Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and finish with maraschino cherries.
Freeze for at least 1 hour or cool for 2 to 4 hours.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 10-inch pie plate on bake pan (grease).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container.

title: randy's lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Place in cold water until ready to use.
Saute beef, pork sausage, onion and garlic; drain off fat.
Add olive oil, tomato puree, tomato paste, seasoning salt, pepper, parsley, basil and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: high fiber granola breakfast cereal
directions: For this amount you will need two, 9 x 13 inch baking pans. Mix together the oatmeal and bran and toast in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Mix together the honey, oil, water and almond extract. Toss the honey mixture with seeds, add dates and nuts, if using. Then toss this together with oats mixture.	Mix until well incorporated.
Return to the oven and bake for 20 minutes more, stirring every few minutes.
When the baking is done, add the raisins.

title: scottish meat pie
directions: Prepare your favorite homemade bread dough or use Rich's frozen bread dough, thawed.
Butter a 10-inch pie dish well. Press dough into bottom and up sides of dish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fudge krispies("they taste like a nestle crunch bar.")
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butter and corn syrup in medium saucepan. Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar. Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until coated. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Chill until firm. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 bars.

title: cajun baked catfish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.

Dredge fillets in mixture. Place skin side down on greased baking sheet. Combine Cajun seasoning and seasoned salt. Sprinkle over the fillets. Drizzle with butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden and fish flakes. Garnish with lemon wedges on plates to serve. Serves 4. Preparation Time: About 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine diced chicken and juice with other ingredients; put in a 9-inch baking dish.
Slice 3 to 4 hard-boiled eggs and put on top.
Top this with 2 cups crushed potato chops.
Bake in a 450° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze meat, then slice thin in 1/4 x 2-inch pieces. In large bowl, combine soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and pepper to taste.
Add beef; toss to coat well.
Let stand several hours in refrigerator.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.
In wok or skillet, heat ginger and garlic in oil.
Add beef; stir-fry about 5 minutes. Remove beef with slotted spoon.
Add vegetables to skillet, 1 or 2 kinds at a time, stir-frying each for 3 to 4 minutes.
When all vegetables have been cooked, except tomatoes, return all to the skillet or wok.
Combine reserved marinade, broth and cornstarch. Pour over mixture and cook until bubbly.
Add tomatoes and cook until heated through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine egg, milk, sugar and oil in a large bowl.
Add pancake mix; stir just until mix is moistened.
Spoon into well-greased muffin cups, 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot water.
Blend in coffee and liqueur.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla and cool slightly.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Add sugar; beat until stiff and not dry.
Gently fold egg white mixture into chocolate mixture.
Turn into crust; freeze until firm.
Top with whipped cream when serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach with onion until thawed.
Beat eggs and milk. Add other ingredients and mix with spinach.
Bake in greased casserole 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate shortbread logs
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Using about 1 teaspoon of dough for each cookie (rolled into a log), bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Melt chocolate and shortening over hot, not boiling, water.
Remove from heat.
Dip ends of cookie in chocolate and then nuts.
Place on waxed paper until firm.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, butter, Karo syrup, salt and vanilla for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: texas tortillas
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream. Add olives, chilies, pimentos, green onions, cheese and jalapeno. Spread on tortillas. Roll up and slice. Serve with hot sauce.

title: broccoli-cheese-noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat butter.
Add onion and saute for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, until cubes dissolve.
Add broccoli (chopped) and garlic powder.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add milk and pepper.
Stir constantly.
Makes 4 quarts.
May be frozen.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown beef, drain.
Add green peppers and onion.
Add chopped tomatoes, beans, chili powder and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer 15 minutes. Serve over corn chips with lettuce.

title: fruit jam
directions: In a large bowl stir together sugar and fruit.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil for 30 minutes.

title: time-out macadamia cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until smooth.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; stir until a soft dough forms.
Stir in white chocolate and macadamia nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Store in an air tight container. Yields:
about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and Crisco thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat all the ingredients about 5 minutes.
Add almond flavoring.
Add vanilla flavoring.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter and sage.
Pour over fish. Marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Remove fish from marinade, reserving marinade.
Broil fish until it flakes easily when tested with a fork, brushing occasionally with marinade.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and spread evenly in a 9-inch pie shell.
Place in refrigerator until set. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool. Top with whipped cream.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, milk, salt and pepper until creamy. Slice cucumbers into mixture and toss to coat. Chill and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: 1. Cook onion, green pepper, and celery in cooking oil until tender.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Mix. 2. Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Heat throughly in a 350° oven.
Yields 6 servings.

title: have-a-heart cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 3 pans or as many as you like with vegetable spray.
Divide frozen dough into 3 equal parts; freeze 2 parts while you work.
Press dough evenly into 1 of the pans. Gently push to the edge.
Repeat steps with other dough.
Bake cookies for 12 to 15 minutes; cool.
Frost cookies; press candies into cookies.

title: summer salsa
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill for up to 4 hours, stirring once or twice.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups salsa.

title: grandma's chew bread(recipe is over 100 years old)
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in a heavy saucepan, stirring well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring mixture well.
Spoon mixture into a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and cut into squares.
Yield: about 3 dozen.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix in order given.
Store in fridge for 4 to 5 weeks.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not grease.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli stems 3 minutes; cook flowers 2 minutes.
Chill in cold water.
This can be done ahead of time.
Put broccoli in large bowl; add diced, hard-boiled eggs, celery and onion, cut in thin slices; two kinds of olives, the mayonnaise and creamy Italian dressing to taste.
You can also season with salt and pepper.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a Pyrex dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Combine rice and soups.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and parsley together.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes (30 minutes covered and rest uncovered) at 350°.

title: pie dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg and lemon juice and add enough water to make 3/4 cup.
Add egg mixture to flour and shortening.
Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
Stays well in refrigerator for several days. May divide dough and freeze.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Note:
If nuts are omitted, add an additional 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: hazel's spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large saucepan.
Simmer and serve warm.

title: cocoa oatmeal drops
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk in boiler; bring to a boil at medium-high temperature.
Boil for about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off stove and add margarine and oatmeal.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, combine margarine, water, Wesson oil and cocoa. Let it come to a boil and mix well with flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: alice's jello cookies
directions: *Flavor of Jello depends on color you want cookies to be.
If you want 2 different colors, use only 1/2 pkg. of each color after dividing dough in half.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream together sugar, milk, egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Salt and boil macaroni and let cool.
Add shrimp, peas and celery to cooled macaroni.
After mixing cream cheese and mayonnaise together, toss with other ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: mary's apricot balls
directions: Grind or finely mince apricots; add coconut and condensed milk.
Mix well.
Make into 1 inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in air tight container.

title: basting sauce for chicken or turkey(no salt)
directions: Mix and pour over bird.
Bake as usual.

title: pecan cookie
directions: Mix and spread on cookie sheet with sides.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread with spatula to wafer thin thickness.
Pour egg white, unbeaten on mixture.
Spread with fingers; pour off excess. Sprinkle 1 cup pecans over top. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hearth bread
directions: Cream together butter, poppy seed and mustard.
Butter between sourdough slices; save some butter for outside of bread.
Put a Swiss cheese slice between each.
Use remaining butter and put 1/2 strip bacon on top of each slice.
Place on foil but keep top open.
Put foil on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Pull apart to serve.
Delicious!

title: chocolate chip pie mix(teacher gift idea)
directions: Combine sugar and flour; seal in airtight plastic bag.	Place chocolate chips, coconut, and pecans in an airtight plastic bag; seal.
Place both bags in a gift container.
A pie plate wrapped in cellophane makes a great gift!

title: strawberry kuchen
directions: Cream 1/3 cup shortening and sugar.
Sift and add salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix together milk, vanilla and egg.
Add, alternating with flour mixture.
Place whole berries over.
Blend flour, oleo and sugar.
Put on top.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: christmas keeping cake
directions: Heat oven to 300 degrees. Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg yolks until light and fluffy. Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Beat into butter mixture. Combine 2

1/2 cups flour and spices. Add to creamed mixture with jam. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Combine remaining flour with pecans, raisins, and dates. Fold into batter. Pour into well greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake 3 to 3

1/2 hours or until tooth pick inserted into center of cake comes out clean. Place cake on wire rack to cool. When completely cool, take piece of cheese cloth large enough to wrap cake completely. Soak cloth in Brandy. Remove cake from pan. Wrap cake tightly with soaked cheese cloth. Tightly wrap in aluminum foil and allow to age 4 to 6
weeks in cool place.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Combine in saucepan over medium heat 1 cup chocolate chips, condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over prepared crust.
Top with nuts; add remaining 1 cup chocolate chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.

title: buffalo snot
directions: Cube cheese and place in crock-pot on low heat.
Brown hamburger.
Drain fat and add to crock-pot.
Add chili and green chilies.
Mix together over low heat until cheese is melted. Serve warm with your favorite dipping style chip.
This has a nasty name but tastes great!
My wife, Ann, got this one from co-worker, Bob Kenward, when she worked at OTC.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut bread in 1/2 inch sticks.
Place on cookie sheet in 200° oven until dry.
Mix salad oil and peanut butter until well blended.
Roll sticks in oil and peanut butter mixture until well coated, then in brown sugar until well coated.
Put on cookie sheet and place in refrigerator until firm.
Keep covered in cookie tin or other covered container.
Will keep for weeks.

title: super sour potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden and slightly crispy on edges.

title: baked shells
directions: Combine cheeses and set aside.
Brown ground beef or sausage, onion and garlic in large skillet or saucepan.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup of sauce to cooked shells.
Spread 1/2 of shell sauce mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of cheese mixture and 1/2 of remaining sauce.
Repeat, ending with sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When mixture is hot and bubbly, remove foil and bake additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: mom-mom's stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and break off into leaves.
Cook leaves in microwave in a small amount of water for 5 minutes to soften. Season ground beef well with salt and pepper.
Add egg, 1/2 cup bread crumbs and grated onion.
Lay out cabbage leaves, and stuff each leaf with ground beef.
Roll up leaves; secure with toothpicks if necessary.
Cut up remainder of cabbage and put into the bottom of a big pot.
Place cabbage rolls on top.
Add the tomato sauce, bay leaf, cranberry sauce, brown sugar, white raisins and a pinch of sweet-n-sour salts.
Serve with rice.
Delicious!

title: mike's banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine milk and instant vanilla pudding.
Beat on low for 2 minutes.
Add sour cream and whipped cream and blend in.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until wafers soften.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake and cool cake following package directions.

title: spaghetti
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain off grease. Add spaghetti sauce, diced onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Stir well.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt, oregano, basil and red pepper.
Stir.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Then serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Pour rice over this.
Cut up fryer and salt and pepper.
Lay over rice.
Add cream of chicken soup and onion soup.
Add water.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered the first hour.
Uncover the last 30 minutes.

title: griddle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda; cut in butter until mixture is mealy.
Add egg, milk and raisins; mix until all ingredients are moistened and dough holds together.
The dough will be very stiff.
Roll on floured board to 1 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Refrigerate until ready to bake on a griddle.

title: glazed honey carrots
directions: Add salt to water and bring to a boil.
Add carrots and bring back to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and reduce to low heat. Cover and cook until tender.

title: pie filling dessert
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Whip topping according to directions on package and set aside.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add cake pieces. Stir gently to coat cake evenly.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Dice bacon and onions and brown.
Drain and put in a 2 quart baking dish.
Add catsup and brown sugar, fold in green beans. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.

title: beer bread
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Lightly grease loaf pan.
In medium bowl mix flour and beer.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Scrape into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until top is lightly browned and sides pull away from the pan.
Cool on rack.
Store in airtight container up to 3 days.
Freeze up to 3 months.

title: seven-layer bars
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs over melted shortening.
Add butterscotch chips, then coconut flakes, then nuts.
Pour milk over all ingredients in pan.
Do not mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Set aside.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.

title: turnip soup
directions: Fry salt pork until crisp.
Saute onions in fat.
Add water and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add turnips, cook until tender. Do not overcook turnips.
Very thin corn meal dumplings may be added with the turnips, if desired.
Season to taste.
Serves 4.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, mix
sugar,
cornstarch,
flour
and salt. Gradually add hot water,
stirring	constantly.
Cook and stir over high heat until
mixture
comes to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in your chocolate and vanilla. Mix in flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: tortilla stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and all spices.
Add all other ingredients, except tortillas, and simmer for 1 hour.
About 5 minutes before serving, add tortillas, continuing to simmer. Serve hot with cornbread.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Place beans in soup pot. Add water to cover by 2-inches. Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain and discard liquid. Return beans to pot. Add ham and 2 1/2 quarts water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add celery and carrots. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender. In a skillet, saute garlic in butter for 1 minute. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Add cold water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Add to the soup with tomatoes. Simmer another 10 minutes. Yields 14 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump un-drained pineapple into 9 X 13 cake pan, spread evenly Dump in pie filling and spread into an even layer.
Dump dry cake mix in and spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put margarine slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Pour with remaining ingredients into a bowl and mix. Spoon into a greased muffin pan. Bake at 425° until done. Keep rest of dough in refrigerator and use when you want it.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together first five items.
Pour into 9-inch deep unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, then 15 minutes at 275° or until center is set.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter and add to stuffing mix.
Add chicken. In separate bowl, combine soups and broth.
Reserve approximately 1 c. soup mixture to pour over top of casserole; add rest of soup to stuffing & chicken.
Mix well, put in 9 x 13 pan, pour remaining soup over top and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients except baking soda; add the oil. Dissolve soda in a little water and pour into applesauce.
Stir until it foams, then pour into batter and stir to mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dark cherry chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg and beat well.
Add sour milk alternating with flour sifted with soda and salt.
Stir in melted chocolate, cherries (juice included), and nuts.
Turn into greased 8 inch square cake pan and bake in a moderate oven 350° for 55 minutes.
Frost with a chocolate frosting.

title: baked celery loaf
directions: Put celery, parsley, walnuts, onion and green pepper through a food chopper, using coarse blade.
Combine remaining ingredients and fold into celery mixture.

title: sausage rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Heat cream cheese and rotel in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in sausage and heat until cream cheese is melted.
Serve warm with chips.

title: cherry bounce
directions: Mix well in gallon glass jar.
Sit lid on (do not tighten lid; could explode).
Let sit for at least 6 months, stirring occasionally.
May return to whiskey bottle if desired.
After 6 months, you may tighten lid.
I use canning jars or jelly jars.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add egg yolk and cream constantly while adding cheese a tablespoon at a time.
Put drained noodles in a large heated serving bowl.
Add cheese mixture to noodles and season as desired with salt and pepper.
Prepare just before serving as it should be served immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Parboil squash and carrots.
Saute onions in the butter. Drain squash and carrots.
Combine all ingredients in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and hot water.
Chill slightly, then add cranberries, celery and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: jezebel cranberry sauce
directions: Bring to boil first 3 ingredients.
Add cranberries and cook 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Put in horseradish and mustard.
Stir.
Refrigerate.
To serve: Pour cranberry mixture over cream cheese.
Put crackers on side.
Makes enough sauce for 2 batches or 2 packages cream cheese.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and salt.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Add the flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Cook until a soft ball forms in water (232° to 240° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Beat until creamy and drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: baked french toast
directions: Heat oven to 475°. Drizzle melted butter onto 17 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Whisk together milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla and spices. Dip both sides of bread into milk mixture. Place on prepared pan. Pour any remaining mixture over bread. Let stand 20 minutes, turning bread over a couple of times.
Bake at 475° for about 15 minutes, turning once, until puffed and golden.

title: punch
directions: Bring jello, sugar and water to a boil making sure jello and sugar dissolve.
Mix ReaLemon, extract and pineapple juice to jello mixture.
Freeze in a gallon container.
Set out to soften about an hour before serving.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture prior to serving.

title: lemon-blueberry trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into 1/2-inch cubes.
Arrange in a 2-quart dessert bowl.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Pour over pound cake.
Spoon pie filling over pudding and spread whipped topping over pie filling.
Chill; sprinkle with pecans.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add rice, soups, water and vegetable; mix together.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and add all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Boil chicken; let cool.
Pick chicken off the bone.
In a large pot, combine chicken, rice, cream of chicken soup, onion, water, sausage (cut in round pieces) and salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil; turn on low.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Saute ground beef and green hot pepper in oil until tender. Now, add pork and beans, bouillon cube, chili powder, brown sugar and catsup.
Simmer all this together for about 5 minutes.

title: marvelous minestrone
directions: Saute onion until transparent.
Combine next 8 ingredients (garlic through tomatoes).
Add sauteed onion and cook for 10 minutes.
Add parsley, basil, rosemary, tomato juice and beef bouillon.
Puree 1/2 cup kidney beans in blender and add to soup. Add remaining 1/2 cup whole kidney beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add macaroni and barley.
Cook 15 minutes longer.

title: pastitso(greek dish)
directions: Fry hamburger; mash it down and then drain.
Salt and pepper it.
Boil water with olive oil in water.
Put macaroni in and boil for 4 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and dissolve Jell-O in boiler on stove.
Add Coke to Jell-O mixture (it will foam).
Chop pecans and cream cheese.
Cut up cherries.
If pitted, remove pits.
Add cream cheese, pecans, cherries and pineapple to Jell-O mixture. Chill.

title: hulupki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Cook rice; set aside to cool.
Cut out core of cabbages and discard.
Parboil cabbage in large pan.
Drain water and cool. Saute chopped onion in butter or oleo until golden brown.
In large bowl or pan, mix together ground meat, onion, rice and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Core each cabbage leaf vein as you begin to make your rolls.
Put about a heaping tablespoonful of mixture on each leaf; roll up and tuck in sides.
If you have extra cabbage (which I do, some leaves are too small to roll), chop it up and put in bottom of roaster pan.
Arrange cabbage rolls on top of chopped cabbage.
Cut sausage into small pieces and put in roaster with rolls.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes, tomato sauce, ketchup, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add water until almost covering rolls.
Cover pan and cook in oven at 350°.
Cook about one hour.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix noodles and nuts together.
Mix onion, soups, celery, tuna, milk, soy sauce and 1/2 noodle mixture.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle noodle mixture over top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: slow baked stew
directions: Combine the marjoram, rosemary, sage, thyme and sweet basil; add parsley, garlic and chopped red peppers; toss all together with the Swiss chard.

title: fried plantains
directions: Peel the plantains.
Make a cut lengthwise, with your thumb and index fingers push away and out the skin.
Scrape very lightly with a knife.
Cut a one-inch slice, you will get about 8 or 9 slices.
Fry them for about 7 minutes or until they feel soft to the touch.
Smash them on a brown paper bag with your hand.
Put them back in the frying pan and cook, they are ready when golden. Sprinkle with salt, or dip them in melted butter or any sauce of your choice.

title: easy cheesy lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix with fork until moist.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan; grease pan on bottom only.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water.
When grits are cooked, add all other ingredients and mix until smooth and all the cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until well blended. Add peanut butter, vanilla and salt (if desired). Beat well.
Add flour, oats and baking soda.
Mix well. Chill until firm, 6 hours or overnight.

title: spicy nut bars
directions: Cream butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Beat until light.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and half the nuts; mix well.
Dough will be stiff.
Press evenly into a 15 x 10-inch shallow pan.
