Brush top with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with remaining nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to
30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Simmer vegetables until juice is gone and pour into casserole dish. Mix onion, celery, mayonnaise and cheese and spread over vegetables. In a saucepan, melt oleo and add crushed crackers. Put on top of casserole and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fruit on a stick
directions: Mix cream cheese, marshmallow cream and milk until smooth. Thread fruit on wooden skewers.
Serve with dip.

title: jan's rice salad
directions: Cook rice in broth according to directions. Cool. Add next 4 ingredients. Mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste. In small bowl, mix mayonnaise and curry powder well. Stir mayonnaise into salad, mixing well. Chill overnight. Serves 6 to 8.

title: snowball oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs, add sifted dry ingredients. Add vanilla and oatmeal, one cup at a time and mix well.
Chill several hours.
Form dough into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Do not flatten balls.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cookies will not look done, but they will be.

title: supreme pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with paprika, salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown chops on both sides in hot shortening.
Drain off excess fat.
Add 1 cup water, celery and soup mix.
Cover and cook over low heat for 40 to 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Remove chops from skillet.
Combine the flour, parsley and 1/4 cup cold water.
Blend into pan juices.
Add milk and mushrooms.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened and bubbly.
Spoon gravy over chops.

title: apple pie in a bag
directions: You will also need a large (20 x 14-inch) oven cooking bag with nylon tie.

title: double almond ice cream
directions: Combine cream, milk and 3/4 cup sugar in medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is hot. Gradually add 1 cup cream mixture to beaten egg yolks, whisking constantly.
When mixture is smooth, strain into double boiler. Gradually add flour in remaining cream mixture, whisking constantly.
Cook over simmering water, stirring until mixture thickens and coats spoon, about 8 minutes.
Stir in extracts. Cool.
Meanwhile, melt butter and remaining 2 tablespoons sugar in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar begins to bubble (30 seconds).
Add almonds, cook and stir over medium heat until golden and well coated, cool.
Stir almonds into cream mixture.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pecan pie 2
directions: Prick pie shell on sides and bottom.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Combine egg substitute and flour with whisk until completely blended.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans. Whisk to combine.
Stir in pecans.
Place shell on baking sheet. Pour pecan mix into shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 to 40 minutes more.
Cool.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Crush 2 cups corn flakes and pour evenly over potatoes.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of potato soup or mushroom soup

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and set aside.

title: salad dressing cake(chocolate)
directions: Mix together and sift first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar, then salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Mix and beat well.
Pour into two layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch salad
directions: Shred lettuce and dice tomatoes.
Drain and rinse Ranch Style beans.
Mix all the ingredients together, adding the chips and dressing right before serving.
Great with barbecue.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Select a young tender turkey (the older they get, the tougher they are) and stuff him with all the ham you can get into him. Baste in syrupy ego.
Add a pinch of humor and a pound of smiles.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in water, bouillon cubes, 1 stick butter, salt and pepper.
When chicken is ready, remove from broth.
Cut tortillas into long strips.
Add to broth.
Debone chicken and add to broth.
Lower heat and add 2 sticks of butter and half and half.
Cook until thickens.
Cover with pie crust and brown in oven.
Serve over rice.

title: oven-fried crappie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix yogurt, mustard and lemon juice.
Dip dish into mixture, coat with chips and place in buttered baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serves 4.

title: angel food candy
directions: Boil on medium heat to 290°.
Quickly add baking soda.
Stir very fast, when it foams, pour on buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces and dip in chocolate.
Makes a large batch.
Be sure you use a large pan, it expands a lot!

title: matterhorn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil, vinegar and garlic salt; gently toss until well mixed.
Combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Toss with salad.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and add rice.
Brown.
Add mushrooms that have been drained and chopped fine.
Stir until almost brown.
Add 1 can of onion soup and 1/2 can of water.
Pour into casserole. Cover and bake about 30 minutes at 350° until most of the moisture is gone.

title: caramels
directions: Mix the Karo syrup and sugar with 2 cups cream.
Heat to soft ball stage. Add 2 cups cream slowly and continue to cook to soft ball stage.
Add last 2 cups of cream and cook to hard ball stage. Pour immediately onto a greased cookie pan.
One end of pan can be covered with walnuts, which will help loosen caramels from pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bourbon, in a large bowl. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until desired serving temperature is reached, stirring every 5 minutes.
Garnish with orange or lemon slices, if desired.

title: john wayne casserole
directions: Cube bread and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over bread cubes; cover with remaining bread. Combine cooled scalded milk and beaten eggs.
Add seasonings and meat; pour over bread.
Pour melted butter over top (optional). Bake at 400° in a water for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion until soft.
Add cheese, margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook in casserole dish 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: company rice
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper; add sausage and brown. Drain excess liquid.
Add rice and noodle soup mix and boiling water.
Put in large casserole dish.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix salad dressing or mustard and cream with 1/2 cup sugar.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Pour into 1 or more baking dishes.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° until top is slightly browned and mixture is bubbling.
Spread on crackers. Excellent party dip.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beef and onion in small amount of oil.
Brown and drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice thin to medium.
Spray 8 x 10-inch glass dish with Pam.
Layer potatoes in dish.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle parsley and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: western beef stew
directions: Combine soups and water.
Put meat in large casserole pan; cover with liquid.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, no peeking.
Serve over rice or noodles with vegetables as desired.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Take each chicken breast and dip in beaten egg and bread in bread crumbs.
Brown breaded chicken in a skillet over medium heat until golden brown.
Remove from pan onto paper towels.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass is better).
Spread sliced mushrooms over the chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mushrooms. Pour chicken broth over everything.
Wrap foil over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour with foil on and an additional 1/2 hour with foil off.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes and sauce.	Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Combine juice, orange rind and shortening; stir in egg.
Pour into dry mixture.
Mix enough to combine.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees, and bake for 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in the center of the cake.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Have cream cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix thoroughly.
Add spices and garlic.
Serve with crackers, French bread or raw vegetables.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Add vanilla.
Let cool completely.
Set aside.
Cream together the granulated sugar, Crisco and butter.
Cream until it looks white and very creamy. Add flour mixture.
Beat until it's creamy.

title: apple butter salad
directions: Heat water and dissolve gelatin in water.
Add salt; chill until it starts to thicken.
Add the apple butter and pour into a greased mold.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with a spoonful of mayonnaise on top.

title: harvard beets
directions: Fry 4 c. raw cubed potatoes in 3 Tbsp butter or oil.
Cook 1/2 medium onion, chopped with potatoes.
Add 1/2 ring cubed, smoked sausage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until done.
Melt 1/2 c. cheddar cheese over top.
Can be served with fries, eggs or anything desired.

title: potato and broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, carrots, onion, broccoli, parsley, bouillon and seasonings. Mix well. Cover. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until veggies are tender. Gradually add milk to mixture. Add cornstarch to small amount of milk, then pour in. Cook until thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, vanilla, sugar and raisins in a deep ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle on nutmeg, dot with butter.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir once or twice in the first hour, once at the last 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter; add soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add onion and broccoli.
Stir in 1/2 cup crumbs.
Place in a greased casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Simmer tips in margarine and water until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute peppers, onions and garlic in margarine until tender.
Drain tips and add to sauteed ingredients.
Add gravy mix to juice from tips and cook until desired thickness.Add to tips. Serve over rice if desired.

title: apple salad
directions: Cut apples and snicker bars into bite size pieces.
Add drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Stir all together.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain meat and add mushroom soup. Simmer meat mixture.
Boil potato cubes until tender.
In large bowl, cream potatoes, margarine and milk.
Add salt to taste.
In 9-inch casserole bowl, layer meat mixture, potatoes, then shredded cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake until cheese is slightly melted.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Mix other ingredients and add to meat.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on buns.

title: janet's easy cheesecake
directions: Grease a large pie pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, eggs and 1 cup of sugar.
Beat until very smooth.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove and let set until it falls a little.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top and place back in oven for 5 minutes.
Chill before serving.
May serve with berries.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Place a layer of cabbage in a casserole and season with salt, pepper and butter.
Cover with a layer of cracker crumbs. Continue until casserole is full.
Finish with a layer of crumbs. Cover with milk which has been preheated.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in oven at 300°.

title: dark yeast bread
directions: Mix shortening, oats, All-Bran, salt, molasses and sugar together and pour the boiling water over this mixture.
Cool until lukewarm, then sprinkle yeast on it and allow to set until tiny beads appear.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour and mix well.
Put 1/2 cup flour on board and knead until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk and punch down and put in pans.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: incredible new york cheesecake(not for the faint of heart)
directions: Cream together the Ricotta and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave cake in to cool for another hour.
Do not open oven door until the whole 2 hours are finished!

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cook the rhubarb, 1 cup sugar and water together until the rhubarb is tender.
Keep hot.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Break up sausage meat into small pieces.
Allow to stand at room temperature until softened.
Mix in cheese and Bisquick with hands and thoroughly blend mixture until it can be formed into a large ball.
Pinch off small pieces and roll to form balls, about the size of large marbles.
Place on baking sheet not touching and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until balls are puffed and golden brown (bake on lowest rack in oven).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with cut up broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, peppers or your choice of veggies.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef. Stir in flour and garlic and then gradually stir in beef broth, stirring until mixture thickens. Cook egg noodles; drain. Slowly blend sour cream into meat mixture, heating thoroughly (don't boil). Serve stroganoff over hot noodles. Serves 4.

title: date pudding
directions: *Put two boxes of cooked vanilla pudding if you use one cake and four if you use two in layers.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Heat milk, sugar and salt to boiling; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add diced marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan.

title: sal's pickled beets
directions: Using large shallow pan, mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Add vinegar, cloves, ketchup, oil, salt and vanilla and mix well.
Add beets and beet juice.
Preheat burner.

title: pork soup
directions: Cut pork in 1/2-inch cubes.
Shake with flour in a plastic bag until coated.
Heat oil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add pork.
Brown lightly.
Add onions; saute 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add celery, bouillon cubes, watter and marjoram.
Bring to boiling, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and mushrooms to liquid.
Bring to a boil again, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and pimientos.
Simmer for 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Crush graham crackers to form crumbs.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Press remainder into 9-inch pie plate.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Boil together cocoa, butter, water and Crisco oil.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Stir well and add buttermilk, eggs (slightly beaten), salt, soda and cinnamon. Mix well. Pour in greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Start making icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: good old southern pintos(old - 1940)
directions: Use cooking apples.
Wash, slice and fry in bacon drippings. Sprinkle heavily with sugar and a little salt.
Fry until done, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Fry in heavy skillet.

title: tangy chicken
directions: * Orange juice is good, too.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a rolling boil and boil exactly 3 minutes.
Add the fluff, peanut butter and vanilla.
Turn into a buttered 8x8 pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut fish into cubes.
Dice potatoes.
Chop onions.
Add parsley and tomatoes.
Put these ingredients into a pot with the water.
Add the salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling and then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, add butter and cream.
Heat until butter melts.

title: browned beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat. Dust with flour. In large skillet, brown meat in fat until very brown. Add stock or bouillon and Dr. Pepper. Cook over low heat until tender. Add all vegetables except peas and cook until barely tender. Add peas and cook at least 10 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: caramel nut popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn and nuts in a large shallow pan and place in preheated 250° oven.
Combine butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Boil until mixture reaches 248° (firm ball stage), about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour mixture over corn and nuts, stirring gently to coat.
Return glazed popcorn and nut mixture to oven and bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
When cooled, pack in airtight tins.
Makes slightly more than 2 1/2 quarts crunch.

title: pineapple coconut pie (makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix ingredients in order by hand.
Pour into two unbaked shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hanky-panky
directions: Mix, brown and drain the beef and sausage.
Mix the cheese with the well drained meat.
Stir well, allowing cheese to melt throughout meat.
Spread on 1 1/2 loaves of party rye bread. Place on cookie sheet and under broiler until brown.
May also be frozen and taken out individually when needed.
If freezing, do not cook until you are serving.

title: chilled cherry soup
directions: Cook the cloves, salt, sugar, cinnamon and the juice of the lemon for 1/2 hour in the water.
Drain, reserving the liquid.
Add the wine.
Blend the flour well with the cream and add to the liquid.
Bring to the boil.
Add the cherries, reserving some for garnish.
Bring to the boil again.
Serve chilled.
Decorate with whipped cream and cherries.
Serves 5.

title: grilled teriyaki salmon
directions: Put seasoning on fish with 1/8 cup of water. Marinate overnight, skin side down. Place salmon on grill, medium-low, skin side down. Grill for 10 to 12 minutes, basting with olive oil every few minutes. Put onion rings on salmon 5 minutes into cooking. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese after salmon is removed from grill. Serves 4.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all together and roll out on floured board cut in thin strips.
Drop in boiling broth.
Use chicken, turkey or beef as you wish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine; add sugar, then eggs.
Mix well, then add buttermilk with baking soda dissolved in it.
Add crushed bananas and a pinch of salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts, then add flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pans.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks until thick and add to sugar and flour.
Combine with evaporated milk, vanilla and milk.
Beat egg whites stiff and add last.
Pour into 6-quart container of ice cream freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yield: 6 quarts.

title: no mayo macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Strain and add ingredients.
Season to taste with Mrs. Dash.
Best when left to set several hours or overnight.

title: scrambled eggs au gratin
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour until smooth. Slowly add 3 cups milk.
Simmer and stir constantly until thick and smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute mushrooms in lemon juice. Beat eggs with milk.
Melt remaining butter and pour eggs in pan, stirring over medium heat until tender.
In greased large and shallow casserole, combine cheese, mushrooms, crumbled bacon, eggs and sauce, stirring to blend.
Can be refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle 1 package soup mix on the bottom of a casserole dish. Sprinkle rice next.
Put the chicken soup and 2 cans water in separate bowl and mix, then place on top of rice.
Place chicken parts next.
Sprinkle the second package of soup mix over the top. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; uncover and cook for another 1/2 hour.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar, butter and salt in glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes, until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn in large glass bowl.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes longer. Cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin mix together.
Add remaining ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased bread pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.
Bread is done when you can insert a knife into the center and it comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie shell.
Dot top with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife comes clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: sweet freezer pickles
directions: Let cucumbers and onions stand 2 hours in 2 tablespoons salt. Stir occasionally.	Pack cucumbers and onions into containers. Heat sugar and vinegar enough to melt sugar.
Pour over cucumbers and freeze.
Makes 4 pints.

title: bread dumplings
directions: Dice and fry bread in butter until crisp.
Remove and place on paper towel.
In large bowl, mix flour and salt.
Mix egg and milk and stir into flour mixture.
Form into dumplings around bread cubes, using 3 to 4 cubes per dumpling.
Drop into boiling water, taking care that dumplings do not stick.
Cover and boil gently 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Reserve chicken broth and debone chicken.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth adding water if needed.
Drain.
Melt the margarine in a skillet and cook onion and pepper until tender.
Add chicken and simmer with a lid on for about 10 minutes.
Mix cooked spaghetti with chicken mixture.
Add mushroom soup and mix well.
Put into a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake about 20 to 30 minutes at 325° or until cheese is melted and everything is blended together.

title: meat balls in gravy
directions: Mix ground meat, celery, onion, egg, salt and pepper well. Bake meat balls in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix mushroom soup and milk together; pour over meat balls in casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
I recommend serving over hot, buttered noodles.

title: frozen pudding-wiches
directions: Pour milk into a small mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until blended for 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on one cookie or cracker.
Press another on top. Freeze until firm about 4 hours.
Wrap for the freezer, keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In a blender container, place Egg Beaters, potatoes, onion, flour and pepper.
Blend until the mixture is evenly rough in consistency.
Melt 1 teaspoon margarine on hot griddle for every two pancakes; pour 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle for each pancake.
Fry on both sides until well browned, about 3 minutes per side.
Serve hot with applesauce, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cookies, together and chill for 2 hours.
When ready to serve, crush cookies and mix in.

title: swiss steak gravy
directions: Stir flour, salt, pepper & shortening over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add liquids and stir until thickened.
Pour over swiss steak.
Serves 6.

title: bite-size bacon quiche
directions: Cook diced bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels and drain.
Cool.
Beat eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Into each tart sprinkle some bacon and spoon in about 1 tablespoon egg mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve immediately.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine corn, milk, sugar, flour, egg yolks, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until frothy, about 1 minute.
Add to corn mixture. Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° to 350° until top is brown and bubbly.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: artichoke hearts
directions: Place artichoke hearts in baking pan.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and oregano. Cover artichokes with mixture. Pour olive oil over.
Sprinkle with a few drops of water.
Bake in moderate oven (350°), until crumbs are golden, approximately 30 minutes.

title: mom's fruit cocktail bars
directions: Grease and flour bottom of cookie sheet.
Beat eggs and sugar at high speed in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add fruit cocktail with juice, flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Spread into pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
While hot, drizzle with glaze.

title: harolyn's breakfast egg dish
directions: Mix all the ingredients; pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan, either greased or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with warm flour tortillas and picante sauce or your favorite salsa.
Good for company.

title: microwave chicken stew
directions: In large covered microwavable dish, put soup and 1 can of water.
Using a wire whisk, stir until smooth.
Add Kitchen Bouquet to desired color.
Chop celery and onion and add to mixture.
Coat chicken pieces with Season-All.
Place in soup mixture and cover.
Microwave for approximately 30 minutes or until done.
(This will depend on the wattage of your microwave oven.)
Serve with rice.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese. Add combined milk and eggs; mix just until moistened.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Combine all ingredients listed. Cook until right consistency of your choice. Also can add meat, if desired. Serve with pita bread wedges, slightly toasted.

title: sherbet cookie pie
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and butter.
Pat mixture into bottom of cake pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and crumble with fork.
Pat into pie pan.
Pack sherbet on top of cooled crust.
Combine thawed Cool Whip, cookies and nuts. Blend thoroughly.
Spread over top of pie.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin or zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin batter.
Bake in loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake about 1 hour.

title: coconut salad
directions: Mix, cover with French dressing, chill and serve in lettuce shells or in scooped-out tomatoes.

title: yummy yummy salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Chill until syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients; let set before serving.

title: quick chicken curry
directions: In a large skillet, add all ingredients, keep stirring, until hot.
Add chicken; heat over low heat until hot.
Serve with hot rice and Mango Chutney.

title: tennessee sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well before applying to pie.
Let cool.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except onions and cheese.
Mix in onions by hand.
In baking dish, layer mix 2 times.
Add cheese.
Repeat until gone.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked reuben chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a greased baking pan, place chicken and season with salt and pepper.
Spoon sauerkraut evenly over each chicken breast.
Place a slice of cheese over each breast and pour salad dressing over cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and Crisco.
Using pastry mixer or knives, cut into pea sizes.
Add egg, vinegar and water.
Blend. Refrigerate until needed.
Makes 3 or 4 pie shells.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat on medium speed.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain, then add pizza sauce.
In casserole dish, put a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Then put hamburger mixture over top of that, add pepperoni next, then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Last, you roll out crescent rolls and lay them on top.
Bake according to temperature on crescent rolls.
Cook until rolls are done and cheese has melted.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 8 ingredients; add remaining ingredients to dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Sift cream of
tartar,
soda,
sugar,
salt
and baking powder with flour.
Rub butter and lard in like for pie crust. Add currants, eggs and milk, add more milk if necessary.
Roll and cut.
Bake
over low flame (350°) about 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: brunch cake
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream.
Add cake mix.
Combine frosting with oleo and add to cake mixture.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Cut in 6 tablespoons butter.
Pat mixture into an ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in 1/2 cup brown sugar, pecans, corn syrup, 2 tablespoons melted butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, leaving out salt. Drain and put in casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Mix the remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour the mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and again dot with butter.
Bake at 325° or 350° for about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and melt.

title: rosemary fizz
directions: Take 1 cup pineapple juice and add crushed rosemary leaves; heat to a boil and let steep.
Strain and cool.
Mix all ingredients, add the ginger ale before serving.
Float lemon slices, decorated with rosemary leaves.

title: white bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and shortening until very warm, 120° to 130°.
Shortening does not need to melt. Add to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until blended.
Beat 3 minutes.
By hand stir in enough flour to make firm dough.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide into two parts.
Roll each into a 14 x 7-inch rectangle, starting with short side; roll tight.
Put into greased loaf pan, turning to grease top to let rise again until dough gets to top of loaf pan, about 30 minutes.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and the loaves have a hollow sound when tapped.

title: fancy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer with vanilla wafers and pudding, ending with pudding on top.
Top with coconut.

title: hot dogs
directions: Put it in a pan and mix it.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Make pudding according to package.
Break up chocolate cakes and place half in large bowl.
Spread/pour half pudding over cake, followed by half Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Break up Skor toffee bars and sprinkle over top layer (Cool Whip).

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions.
Cook over low heat until onions are soft.
Add paprika.
Make roux by browning the oil and the flour mix, being certain it is evenly browned.
Add the onions, roux, celery salt, salt and pepper to beef stock and stir until it boils.
Let simmer for at least 2 hours.
Add beer.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and add the remaining ingredients. Let simmer in crock-pot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; add dry ingredients (flour, oats, raisins, nuts, soda and salt). Mix well.
Spoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 40 to 50 cookies.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: truffle mice
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream.
Add wafer crumbs; mix well. Chill for 1 hour or until firm.
Roll by teaspoonfuls in confectioners sugar.
Shape into an oval for body of a mouse. Place 2 gold or silver shot candies for eyes, 2 almonds slices for ears and desired length of licorice whip for tail.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Mix chicken, sour cream and cream of chicken soup together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: lemon drops
directions: Mix whipped cream, sugar and egg until gooey.
Spoon on greased pan.
Lay pecan on top.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix thawed lemonade, lemon juice, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into pie crusts.
Chill several hours.

title: welca slaw dressing
directions: Mix well, then add 1/3 cup of mayonnaise.
This is also good on fruit.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in milk; place on heat and stir constantly until comes to boil and bubbles for 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco, Crisco oil, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together cream of tartar, baking soda, salt and flour.
Add flour mixture to other mixed ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (5 and 5) on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll into small balls, then roll in sugar.
(Can use colored sugar.) Press down with bottom of glass.
(Glass in sugar
cookie spreads out.)

title: red wine and brandied mandarins
directions: Peel mandarins and slice horizontally.
Sprinkle both sides with sugar, cover with red wine.
Marinate the mandarins for at least 2 hours.
Serve as part of green salad or as a side dish for paella.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except raisins; add raisins.
Grease and flour bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken with garlic
directions: Brown chicken in butter and olive oil.
Add 40 cloves of garlic and saute over very low heat until garlic is semi-transparent.
Do not brown garlic as it often causes bitterness.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in wine and stock and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with remaining sauce.
Serve with rice and tossed salad.

title: clam pie
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Mix the first 4 ingredients. When well blended, add clams.
Spread in pie plate and sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese and lightly with dry parsley flakes. When ready to serve, bake in 325° preheated oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with Wheat Thins or heavy chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown garlic, onion and beef in oil and drain. Add spaghetti sauce, water, sugar, salt, pepper, oregano and basil to beef and simmer 30 minutes.

title: nut bars
directions: Cream oleo with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well, then add flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Add chocolate chips and pecans or walnuts.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes in a well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan or until soft to the touch, but well done around the edges.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush mushrooms with salad oil.
Stuff mushrooms.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in a buttered baking dish.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients slowly. Roll into log.
Wrap and chill.
(Do not freeze!) Slice and bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
This will keep in refrigerator 3 months!

title: 5 layer dip
directions: To make first layer, combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
To make second layer, combine cream cheese and picante.
To make third layer, combine avocados, pepper, lemon juice and garlic salt to taste (1/4 teaspoon+).
To make fourth layer, combine Cheddar and Jack cheeses by tossing together.
To make the final layer, mix black olives and tomato.

title: easy mint brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, mix together butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs and stir until blended.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture and blend well. Reserve 2 cups batter and set aside.
Spread remaining batter in prepared pan.
Place peppermint patties in a single layer over batter, about an inch apart.
Spread reserved batter over patties.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut into 36 bars.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour in large pan; make a well or hole.
Add sugar, shortening and eggs.
Combine baking powder and soda in buttermilk; let it start bubbling before combining with other ingredients.
Add salt to flour and flavoring in the eggs.
Do not beat eggs separately.
Work in stiff dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: lily sandwiches(party)
directions: Dice chicken and combine with celery, onion, tarragon, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Cut bread into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Spread bread with softened butter or oleo and then roll up cornucopia style, overlapping the two adjacent edges.
Secure with a toothpick.
Spoon in chicken filling.

Place close together on a plate; cover with plastic wrap and chill for at least 1 hour. Before serving, remove toothpicks; sprinkle with chopped parsley and insert carrot stick for the stamen in each lily.
Makes 18 sandwiches, about 130 calories each.

title: 7 layered dip
directions: Heat beans and picante sauce and set aside.
Layer the bean mixture, guacamole, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, black olives and tomatoes.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to package directions. Cool and crumble cornbread into large mixing bowl. Add chopped onion, diced green pepper and diced tomato. Fold in Miracle Whip. Serve immediately or chilled. Add crisp bacon if desired.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the butter, sugar and eggs, then add other ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Whip up cream cheese with fork until creamy.
Add all other ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Mix and form in ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: graham cracker salad
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in double boiler.
When melted, cool.
Then add whipped cream and fruit cocktail.
Melt butter and pour over crushed graham crackers.
Line dish with crumbs.
Put in cream mixture and top with a few crumbs.
Set in refrigerator until set.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 7
ingredients; pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle butter over cake.
Sprinkle pecans over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut patties
directions: Put ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Then just as it starts boiling, turn fire down very low (just bubbling).
Time for 1 hour, stirring about every 10 or 15 minutes.
Take off fire and add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 teaspoon butter and red food color to make pink for peanut patties (none for pralines).
Beat until creamy (I just keep stirring until it gets kind of sticky), about 10 or 15 minutes.
By spoonfuls, make patties on waxed or foil paper.
They will have to set several hours before they get hard. (I leave mine overnight.)

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix and pour over roast.
Cook 4 to 5 hours at 325°.
Keep covered while cooking.

title: spinach salad
directions: To cooked rice, add salad dressing, soy sauce and sugar; mix well.
Cover and chill until cold.
Chop spinach, celery and onion and stir into cold rice mixture.
Just before serving, sprinkle bacon pieces on top.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the 2 packages of jello in 1 cup of boiling water. Add undrained fruits to jello and stir well.
Congeal.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix with sugar.
Add sour cream.
Spread over congealed jello and top with nuts.
Serves 12.

title: cheese pit
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread both sides with oleo.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with meat of your choice; top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat and cheese.
Chill at least 8 hours (better overnight).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut crust off of bread and roll out each slice with rolling pin until flat; set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, egg yolk and 1/4 cup sugar until well blended. Spread onto bread slices and roll them up into rolls.
In small bowl mix together 1 cup sugar and enough cinnamon to your liking; roll bread rolls into butter and then into the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.
(Can also be put in freezer with cookie sheet until ready to bake.)

title: spinach dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mix together.
Rinse spinach and "loosen" it.
Add spinach pieces to sour cream mixture.
Add in bell pepper and cheese.
Mix well. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cold zucchini soup
directions: In a food processor, combine tomatoes, green pepper, zucchini, celery, onion, lemon, basil and cumin.
Process with on/off turns until smooth.
Serve chilled.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks. Sift flour three times. Add soda to sour cream.
Stir well. Add flour and cream alternately to sugar and egg mixture. Beat egg whites, fold into batter. Put in tube pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch rectangular baking pan, mix soup and water. Sprinkle the rice throughout mixture.
Place cut up chicken in pan.
Pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until rice and chicken are cooked.

title: microwave peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in 8 x 8-inch microwavable dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches. Microwave uncovered, on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn. Microwave 4 to 6 minutes longer.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onions. Drain well. Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Simmer, covered, for at least 2 hours or longer. Serves 10.

title: chicken 'n chillies casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, light cream, onion, chilies, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, chicken and 2 cups of the cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger junk
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Spread in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Layer onion, peas, potatoes, salt, pepper and mushroom soup.
In saucepan, melt oleo.
Add 1 cup water; bring to a boil. Break up bread and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in a buttered casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place on rounds of party rye bread on cookie sheet.
Pop into oven.
Watch until brown and tops are "bubbly".
Serve immediately.
Good with cocktails.

title: rice krispies
directions: Put the marshmallows in a saucepan with the butter.
Melt over low heat, stirring constantly, until completely melted. Remove from heat. Add the Rice Krispies.
Stir until they are coated. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with cooking oil. Cut into squares when cooled.
You may also roll into balls.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Place rolls in

well-greased Bundt pan. Pour melted butter over frozen rolls. Combine pudding mix and brown sugar. Sprinkle over rolls and butter. Sprinkle nuts over top. Leave out overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese coffee cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth. Save 2 rectangles of crescent dough and arrange the other 12 triangles (on 13 or 15-inch round pan) with points in center. Leave points loose and push dough together to form circle.

title: favorite cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong pan.
Mix sugar, baking powder, salt, flour, milk and vanilla.
Mix and pour over the melted margarine and put the peaches which have been cooked on top of the dough mix.
Bake at 325° until dough comes to top and browns nicely. Very nice with ice cream on top.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix
and
freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon. You can
make strawberry by using strawberry soda and substituting 2 cups frozen strawberries for pineapple.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Boil chicken until completely done. Let cool, then remove skin and bones and cut chicken into small pieces. Layer broccoli, then chicken in dish. Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Spread over chicken. Grate cheese over top, then sprinkle bread crumbs or crackers over cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken in melted butter then coat in crumb mix and place skin side up in ungreased 9 x 9-inch dish.

Bake 50 to 60 minutes to tender in 375° oven. Combine other ingredients to leftover butter and when chicken is golden brown, pour butter mix over and continue to bake 5 minutes. Serve and spoon sauce over meat.
Serves 4.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together cheese and margarine.
Add flour and paprika. Work together with hands.
Take 1 tablespoon of dough and wrap around the olives or links.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° on ungreased baking sheet.
May make ahead and freeze.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in uncooked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-calorie zucchini lasagna
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, micro-cook zucchini and 2 tablespoons water, covered, on 100% power (HIGH) for 4 to 6 minutes or until tender, stirring once. Drain in a colander. Set aside.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Boil water, rice, salt and onions until water is gone.
Add oleo, then soup, chicken and milk.
Pour into pan.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick thoroughly to make dough. Make into bite-size balls and bake on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve piping hot.

title: berry pie
directions: Mix
crushed graham crackers, butter and 1/4 cup sugar. Spread in
9-inch pie plate.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and eggs. Pour over graham cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Pour can of pie filling over cooked mixture and chill. Serve with whipped cream.
Serves nine.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and chop into bite-size pieces.
In saucepan, saute finely chopped onion in butter or margarine.
Add mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, evaporated milk, mushrooms, pimento, cheese, salt and pepper and soy sauce.
Place deboned chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with 2 cans drained asparagus spears.
Pour sauce over chicken and asparagus. Sprinkle with parsley, chopped fine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°
or until bubbly.
Serve over rice.

title: m and m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in large bowl. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift remaining dry ingredients and mix together well with sugar mixture. Stir in candies.

title: holiday cookie recipe
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, then add flour and cream together.
Add nuts.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Great at Christmastime!

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into a sprayed 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: marinovannye griby(pickled mushrooms)
directions: In an enameled or stainless steel sauce pan, combine vinegar, cloves, water, peppercorns, bay lef, salt and garlic.
Bring to a boil over high heat, drop in the mushrooms, and reduce the heat to low.
Simmer uncovered, for l0 minutes, stirring mushrooms occasionally, then cool to room temperature.
Remove the garlic and pour the entire contents of pan into a quart jar.
Slowly pour the vegetable oil on top; secure top with plastic wrap and cover the jar tightly.
Marinate in refrigerator for at least a week.

title: lemon cream cheesers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mix until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into bottom of ungreased 8 or 9 inch square pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour over crust.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, cut into bars.
These freeze well.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and flavorings; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in flour; beat well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, and oil in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda, beating until smooth.
Stir in pineapple with juice, bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for several minutes, turn upside on wire rack to cool completely.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut shortening into flour.
Add cold water.
Mix well, roll out and place in pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine 1/2 tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In previous recipe, substitute 2 tablespoons molasses for the milk and cinnamon for nutmeg.

title: ono meat loaf
directions: Soak bread slices in clam juice.
Mix together all ingredients.
Put into a large loaf pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 46 to 60 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake in a glass oblong dish, following directions on box. When cooled, punch holes every 1/2 inch through out cake.
Pour into holes of cake 1 can condensed milk, followed by 1 can of creme of coconut.
Follow this with 1 can crushed pineapple and top with one tub of whipped cream, sprinkle with shredded coconut and refrigerate immediately.
Best served after cake has set for 24-28 hours.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits thin.
Wrap around 1/4 large apple.
Place upside down in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: great northwest pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in single layer in a large shallow baking dish; set aside.
In a small bowl, using fork, beat sugar, Worcestershire sauce, Creole seasoning, oil and vinegar to blend well.
Pour mixture over chops in baking dish, turning chops to coat both sides, rubbing marinade in well.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes or in refrigerator up to 12 hours.
Heat broiler; position rack about 6-inches from heat. Arrange chops on rack in broiler pan; broil 6 minutes on each side until lightly browned.
Also great on grill.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in mixing bowl.	Pour in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and bread crumbs (optional).	Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: progressive dinner chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place one slice ham on each flattened chicken breast and fold cheese to lay in center of ham.
Roll breast and fasten with toothpicks. In small saucepan mix all sauce ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Place chicken rolls in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour, until chicken is fork-tender.
Delicious!

title: texas stew
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion. Roll into balls about 1 1/4-inches in diameter. Brown in skillet on medium heat. Drain excess grease. Add soup, beans, corn, water, mustard and salt. Simmer on low heat 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil.
Remove chicken.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, drained mushrooms, salt, basil, oregano, pepper and bay leaf; mix well. Return chicken to skillet.
Cover pieces with sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add wine; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.

title: orange juice supreme
directions: Pour frozen orange juice and milk into blender.
Scoop in ice cream.
Cover and blend on high for a few seconds.
Makes 3 to 4 shakes.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Let stand until cool. Cream sugar and butter. Add egg
and date mixture.
Add walnuts and flour.
Bake in
a 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: basic ice cream
directions: Mix pudding with milk; beat with mixer until it begins to thicken like custard.
Add sugar and Carnation.
Add fruit, if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil ziti (pasta) 10 minutes.
Drain.
In large pot fry onions in
olive
oil
until
golden.
Add
tomatoes, Italian seasoning and
shredded cheeses. When cheese melts, add ziti. Then
place in
greased
x
13-inch
pan.
Put more cheese (preferably Mozzarella) on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top gets brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix in enough flour to be stiff enough to roll in small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and crisscross with fork. Bake at 350°. Take out of oven while soft in the middle.

title: curried rice and chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients; grease another bowl.
Put dough in, cover with foil and let stand overnight (do not refrigerate).
Next morning, knead a little.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Put into greased pans and brush with oil.
Let rise 4 to 5 hours.
Keep covered with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from pans, brush with butter.
Cool on rack.
Wrap well and store.
Bread may be frozen.

title: mom's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in a large saucepan; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients (except spaghetti).
Cook until onion and celery are tender.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and mix with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole(yield: 8 portions)
directions: 1. Butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Take a plastic container with a lid.
You will have to decide what size you need.
Each day as you have leftover food, put it in the container and store in freezer.
Keep adding leftovers until you have enough to make soup.
Add onion, bell peppers and celery to taste (saute first).
If you need extra liquid, put water or tomato juice in the amount you need to make it as thick as you like.
A small amount of chili or meat sauce added makes it real good.
Also, macaroni and cheese adds to the taste.
If the soup is in the sweet side, add a little vinegar; or if it's too sour, add a little sugar.
Cook until the flavors have blended together.

title: chocolate better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions and bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan. let cake cook for 15 minutes.
Pierce top of cake with a toothpick all over.

title: vegetable cheese bake (eggplant pizza)
directions: In large skillet, heat margarine.
Saute onion and pepper for three minutes.
Add eggplant and mushrooms.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook 1 minute.
Spread stuffing mix over bottom of casserole.
Layer half the vegetable mix, one cup cheese and the remaining half of the vegetable mix.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix liquid with one package of vanilla instant pudding.
Pour over fruit.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain the beans and add all ingredients except sugar and vinegar.
Heat the sugar and vinegar.
Add to bean mixture.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: schnitz and kneppe(schnitz means dried apples and kneppe refers to fluffy dumplings.)
directions: Cover apples and ham with water and simmer 2 hours.
Add brown sugar and simmer 1 more hour.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; mix egg, butter and milk in separate bowl.
Add to flour mixture; drop by tablespoon into simmering ham and apples.
Cover tightly and cook 15 minutes without lifting lid.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Beat until smooth.
Heat cast iron skillet on the stove until hot.
Pour in batter and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken loaf
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until tender.
Cover bread crumbs with
hot broth until dissolved.
Add chicken, eggs and soup.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, cover with topping and melted butter.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: potluck lasagne(lasagne roll-ups)
directions: Remove casings from sausage and crumble.
Brown sausage with onion and garlic in a deep saucepan.
Pour off excess fat.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce, water (wine), oregano, basil and rosemary.
Cover and boil gently for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion, garlic and pepper to taste; set aside.
Brown rice in margarine.
When brown, add water, packages from rice mix, 1/2 cheese, salsa sauce and ground chuck.
Mix together; bring to boil, then lower and cover.
Simmer until done. Stuff parboiled peppers and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan with any extra stuffing.
Sprinkle top with the rest of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut large green tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Coat slices in flour, sugar, salt and pepper mixed together.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra tight in 6 or 7 pint jars.
Bring to a boil all ingredients.
Pour over okra you have packed into jars.
Seal jars.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over lettuce and onions.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in vinegar, catsup and paprika.
Makes 1 cup.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients. Shape into golf ball size. Brown in oil over medium heat.
Turn frequently until completely browned. Remove from frypan.
Drain oil.
Prepare soup per can instructions.
Place meatballs in frypan.
Cover with soup mixture.
Heat over low flame 15 minutes.
Serve atop noodles or over rice.

title: hamburger tofu casserole
directions: Cube into blocks the tofu and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the tofu.
Saute hamburger; add onion and saute until onion is soft and hamburger is done.
Drain off all oil.
Stir in water chestnuts and minced green onions.
Add shoyu, sugar and garlic and simmer until liquid is absorbed.
Pour meat over the tofu. Beat the eggs and pour over entire meat surface.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until eggs are cooked.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients into boiler on top of stove and allow to come to a full boil (stirring all the time).
Remove from stove.
Sift sugar, flour and salt.
Put the flour mixture and vanilla into chocolate mixture, stirring.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk with soda, mixed.
Beat all in mixer.
Grease and flour two long pans (9 x 13 x 2-inch) and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in large bowl.
Add blueberries.
Stir to coat evenly.
In small bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk and butter.
Add to blueberry mixture.
Stir just until blended.

title: miss nettie's raisin cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs and add 4 cups flour.
In a separate bowl, put the raisins and coat with the 1/2 cup of flour. Add raisins, lemon and baking powder to dough and mix well.
Cook at 225° for 2 hours and 25 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and sugar.
In a large bowl, lightly beat the eggs.
Mix in oil and rind.
Stir in the sifted flour mixture until just blended.
Fold in the strawberries and nuts.
Do not overblend or the bread will be tough.

title: herb roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes, onion, green pepper and red pepper into chunks. Mix all ingredients in shallow baking pan, arrange in single layer. Bake until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased oblong baking dish; sprinkle grated cheese over bread.
Sprinkle sausage over cheese and pour margarine over sausage.
Beat eggs with mustard, salt and milk and pour over casserole.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm.
(Bacon or ham may be used in combination with sausage.)

title: chicken superb
directions: Butter good-sized shallow casserole.
Spread beef over bottom of dish.
Arrange chicken breasts neatly on beef.
Top each piece chicken with bacon.
Pour cream and soup mixture over all.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 2 hours.
Remove foil and bake another hour until nicely browned on top.
This is good served with rice.

title: peanut butter delights(no bake)
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except the chocolate chips. Press into a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
(It is easiest to cut into squares while chocolate is still soft.)

title: amazing cookies
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, add sugar.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in vanilla, chocolate chips, and nuts.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheets.
Turn oven off.
Put cookies in oven for at least 3 hours or better if overnight.
Do not open oven until ready to take out.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumb Oreos and set aside.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar and set aside.
Mix milk and vanilla pudding together and fold into Cool Whip and add to cream cheese mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, in a roaster for 3 hours at 325°.
Can use crock-pot.
Check and stir a few times.

title: waldorf salad(method:  fireless)
directions: Wash apples and celery.
Dice celery.
Remove cores from apples and dice (do not peel apples).
Mix apples, celery, nuts and mayonnaise together in a large bowl.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and corn; add onion and mayonnaise.
Pour into casserole bowl and cover with cheese; then crumble crackers over top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot sweet pickles with garlic
directions: Put pickles in large container so they can be stirred often. Pour sugar over pickles with garlic and Tabasco sauce.
Stir often and let set at least overnight.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend margarine.
Add cheese, a little at a time.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add 1 teaspoon water.
Add pepper.
Put in cookie press.
Use star disk.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together; add vanilla and eggs. In a separate bowl, sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add flour and oats alternately to sugar mixture, then add nuts and chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: doris' sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add egg and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly. Measure flour by dipping method or sifting.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough to 3/16-inch thick on lightly floured pastry cloth and cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until delicately golden.

title: brown rice veggie stir fry
directions: In skillet, combine water, soy sauce and oil.
Add the zucchini and onion, stir fry for 4-5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add the rice, tomato and carrot.
Stir fry for 2-3 minutes or until heated through. sprinkle with almonds.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cream cheese flan
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Mix cream cheese with one can water until smooth.
Add to egg mixture.
Then add vanilla and mix well. Set aside.
Put sugar in saucepan and cook on high until sugar caramelizes to brown color.
Pour into center of 9 x 5-inch glass baking dish and shift dish from side to side until sugar covers it completely.
Let sugar cool and harden.
Pour flan mixture into dish.
Put dish into a 13 x 9-inch pan and fill with water until it reaches about halfway up flan dish.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours. Cool and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, invert dish onto larger platter and cut into pieces.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Spoon the bacon, mushrooms and onion onto bottom of shell.
Sprinkle cheese next. Beat eggs.
Add the light cream and spices.
Pour mixture over all.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Knife inserted in middle should come out clean.

title: tropical banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in milk, mashed bananas and pineapple.
In separate bowl, mix flour, bran, baking powder and salt.
Add to banana mix.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add well beaten egg. Mix with sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk and first mixture.
Turn into greased cake pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and chiles to make sauce.
Dip tortilla in hot oil.
Remove and place some chicken, onion and cheese in tortilla.
Roll and place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: almond-hazelnuts biscotti
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except almonds and hazelnuts. Add almonds and hazelnuts.

title: country-style stuffed peppers
directions: Combine contents of rice and seasoning packets, water and butter in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in ham.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until desired consistency.
While rice cooks, cut green pepper in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membranes. Cook in salted boiling water about 5 minutes; drain well.
Fill pepper halves with hot rice mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple nut pound cake
directions: Do not use a mixer.
Combine first 3 ingredients, then add the rest.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: double chocolate cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients, stir into margarine mixture (dough will become stiff).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cherry half into center of each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: potluck melon salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss bananas in lime juice.
Add melon balls, pineapple, grapes, strawberries and coconut.
Layer marshmallows on top.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.
In a 6 1/2-cup service bowl, stir together the yogurt, 1/4 cup lime juice and the honey. Cover and chill for 4 hours.
Just before serving, drain fruit. Stir in yogurt mixture.
Toss to coat well.
Serve immediately.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Toast English muffins.
Mix ketchup, oregano and garlic powder.
Spread on muffins.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chili
directions: Combine ground chuck, sausage, onions, garlic and jalapeno peppers in large pan.
Brown, then drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook over low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve with grated sharp Cheddar cheese on top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sour cream, butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix soda with flour and stir or beat into creamed mixture, gradually, until it is a good consistency to roll out.
Cut out cookies with a cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar on the cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Test baking time according to your oven.

title: beef-noodle cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles, saute onion, beef and pepper.
Mix in tomato sauce.
Butter casserole.
layer noodles on bottom (1/2 of noodles); mix cheeses and sour cream together.
Place on top of noodles.
Put beef mixture next and remaining noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour with cover or with aluminum foil.
This makes enough for 2 meals.
Can be prepared ahead and baked for company.
Freezes well.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Meanwhile, combine tuna, mushroom or celery soup, water and sweet peas.
In ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer noodles, soup mixture and crushed package of salt-free potato chips.
End with the chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with green salad and rolls.

title: ricotta cake con pasta frolla
directions: In bowl, mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add butter and work mixture till it is coarse.
Add beaten eggs and water to make pliable dough.
Gently, by hand, blend ingredients.
Form into two balls; one for bottom and sides of baking dish and one to cover filling.
Wrap balls in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: connie's barbecue spareribs from taiwan
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cut up the spareribs into small pieces; soak overnight in sauce.
Bake in a shallow pan at 275° for about 3 hours, spooning the sauce over the meat occasionally.
You can also cook quickly at 350° for 1 hour, if necessary.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, water, half & half, cheese, flour, onion and pepper in a large saucepan.
Whisk to combine and to break up any lumps of flour, then turn heat to medium/high.
Bring soup to a boil, then reduce heat to low.
Add broccoli to soup and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until broccoli is tender, but not soft.
For each serving spoon one cup of soup into a bowl and garnish with a tablespoon of shredded cheese and a pinch of parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: the oaks restaurant clam chowder
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick skillet.
Add mushrooms along with ginger.
Saute over medium heat until mushrooms are soft. Increase heat to medium-high and add scallops.
Cook for about 3 minutes, stirring often.
For the last minute of cooking, add parsley.
The scallops should be seared on the outside, but still moist on the inside.

title: baked meat patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into 4 patties. Place in greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Use a 9-inch casserole or an 11 x 7 dish.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. Heat candies and milk in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth; remove from heat.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in large bowl.
Stir in margarine with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of the crumbly mixture in pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts; drizzle with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbly mixture over top.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 54 cookies.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Stir undrained pineapple into the cream cheese.
Stir in pudding mix.
Fold in the drained pineapple and Cool Whip; chill.

title: one-minute fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Beat with an electric mixer until fudge stiffens and loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: new england apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350° F. Butter/spray a baking dish and spread apples along bottom.
Sprinkle with orange juice, apple juice or water.

title: *hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Add butter, sugar, salt and hot water.
Heat until all sugar crystals are dissolved. Cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add coffee cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Serve hot over vanilla ice cream.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add 1/2 large container of Cool Whip and mix together. Then layer in big glass bowl: vanilla wafers, banana slices, pudding mixture, vanilla wafers, banana slices, pudding mixture, 1/2 large container Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: crock pot dressing
directions: Mix all together. Pour into crock pot. Dot with one stick of butter. Cook for 2-3 hr on high or on low for 4-5 hr or overnight.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, salt and soda; add to batter.
Roll chips and add nuts. Shape in balls.
Press out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange jello fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Add dark brown sugar; cook until melted.
Add 1/2 cup chopped dates.
Remove from heat.
Add egg; cook for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; mix.
Add Rice Krispies (one cup at a time), then mix in chopped nuts.
Mixture will be cool enough to work into balls, then roll in flaked coconut.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and oleo well.
Blend in flour slowly.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot garlic dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in quart jars.
In each quart, add 1 button of garlic, 2 red peppers and dill to taste.
Mix salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal jars.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix all at once.
Bake in angel food cake pan, floured and greased.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: long bay cheeseburger
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut in 1/2 lengthwise, two 11-inch French rolls.
Put equal parts of meat mixture on cut side of each half roll.
Spread evenly to edges. Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.
During last 5 minutes of baking, top with 4 slices processed American cheese, cut in thirds.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring by hand until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Do not beat with mixer.)
Stir in vanilla and pineapple and 1 cup each of the walnuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into three well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting sprinkling the remaining cup of walnuts and bananas over the top of the icing.

title: poached salmon and sour cream
directions: Make a roux with flour and butter.
Poach salmon in wine and chicken broth.
Remove and place on a platter; keep warm.
Reserve broth.
Using roux, add broth.
Then add sour cream, salt, pepper, dill weed and Worcestershire sauce.
Serve salmon and pass sauce to pour over each portion.
Serves 4.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put 1/2 the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla. Fold two mixtures together and pour into pan on crumbs.
Spread remaining crumbs over top.
Can be served chilled or frozen.
Makes 12 to 15 pieces.

title: egg pie
directions: Heat milk and butter and stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 300° and increase to 350° slowly.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Melt the butter with the dark brown sugar in 3-quart pot.
Cook until it reaches hard crack stage (put on medium heat and stir with wooden spoon so it won't burn).
Use a candy thermometer, hard crack is 300°.
Butter cookie sheet and pour the mixture onto the sheet.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and spread chips with wooden spoon when they start to melt.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans immediately.
After 1 hour, crack into small pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in cubes.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Cook onion in bacon grease.
Heat soup and milk.
Add onion and potatoes. Heat until all are blended.
Serve with crumbled bacon.
If this is too thick, add more milk.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: Chop strawberries in blender; add sour cream, sugar and brandy and blend until smooth, then mix in coffee cream.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, butter, sugar, Karo, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in fat.
Combine other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes to make sauce.
Place browned pieces of chicken in baking pan and pour sauce over it.
Put into medium oven at 350° and bake, uncovered, for an hour, basting frequently.
Test drumstick for doneness and if pink meat shows, bake for 15 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a tube pan that has been greased and well floured.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: north carolina barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the dry mustard and 6 teaspoons water in a small stainless steel or enamel saucepan. Bring to a rapid boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Dissolve the mustard in the cold water, then thin it out with some of the hot vinegar sauce.
Stir the mustard into the sauce.
Let cool and store in the refrigerator.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Divide cake into 3 equal parts.
Break into bite size pieces in separate bowls.
Sprinkle each one with 1/2 to 3/4 package of different color jello.
Toss.
(This is for color and flavor.) Using a tubular cake pan with removable bottom, begin layering:

title: buttermilk pound cake
