directions: Beat egg yolks with 1/3 cup of the buttermilk; add shortening and sugar and beat until it looks like whipped cream.
Sift flour, soda and salt together times.
Mix dry ingredients and remaining buttermilk with sugar mixture, alternating.
Fold in egg whites. Then last, fold in extract.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour and seasonings together.
Roll chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Fry in Crisco oil until done.

title: italian delight
directions: Fry out beef and onion until onion is lightly brown and the beef cooked through. Drain.
Cook the macaroni as package directs. Drain.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: While noodles are cooking, beat egg yolks into cream and grate the cheese.
Melt butter over low heat in a medium saucepan.
Add egg and cream mixture and blend well.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Once liquid is hot enough to melt cheese, gradually add cheese, blending well after each addition.
Do not boil!!
Add salt to taste.
Drain noodles and mix sauce into them. Serve at once.
Garnish with fresh parsley and grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.
Serving suggestion:
Use as a main course with a tossed salad and steamed vegetables.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients, mix well. Pour into greased hot skillet.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: creole corn
directions: Cook corn, onion and pepper in butter until corn is tender or about 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: buttermilk-cornmeal biscuits
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl, cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
On a floured surface, knead dough 5 or 6 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness, cut with 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet coated with Pam.
Brush tops with egg white.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes until golden.
Makes 13 biscuits (112 calories each).

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts in large oven roaster.

title: italian sausage
directions: Add to fresh ground pork, ham or turkey.
Mix all ingredients well and shape into patties.
Good for breakfast, brunch or lunch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Bring water to a boil with 1 teaspoon salt and add broccoli.
Return to a boil and cook for 5 minutes. Add rice and let set for 5 minutes, covered.
Put margarine in a large casserole dish in oven to melt.
Mix remaining ingredients with broccoli and rice.
Stir until Cheez Whiz and chicken soup are dissolved.
Pour in casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and shred potatoes.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt the butter;
pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over melted butter.
Drain pineapple and reserve.
Spread pineapple evenly over brown sugar and butter.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Add 1/3 cup of melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until well blended. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining butter or margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in the pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: low calorie oatmeal-applesauce cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
mixing
well
with electric mixer. Pour into a Bundt pan that
has been sprayed with Pam. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: flaky apple foldovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate
dough
into
biscuits. Press or roll each to
a 4-inch circle.
In small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spoon
about
2 tablespoons apples onto center of each flattened
biscuit.
Spoon 1 teaspoon sugar mixture over apples.
Fold
dough
in half over filling.
Press both sides of each in
butter, then in remaining sugar mixture. Place in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake
at
375° for 15 or 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan to cool.
Serve warm or cool.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter 2 of the 8 slices of bread; cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside.
Cut remaining 6 slices of bread into 1-inch cubes and place in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, onion, celery, green pepper, mayonnaise and salt.
Spoon mixture over bread cubes.
Combine the eggs, milk and soup; pour over all. Sprinkle buttered bread cubes on top.
Chill for 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, add grated Cheddar cheese over the top.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach and drain it; retain liquid. Melt butter on low heat; add flour until smooth but brown. Add onion and cook until soft, then add liquids slowly. Add slowly the seasonings and cheese. Stir together and cook slowly until blended well.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs. Add jam and mix well. Stir in sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar and cream.
Add salt and vanilla.
Put in freezer for 20 minutes.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes 4 quarts ice cream.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand and ReaLemon.
Pour into crust and bake 30 minutes. Chill.
Spread with whipped topping.

title: mexican chocolate ice cream
directions: In double boiler over gently simmering water, melt chocolate. Stir until smooth.
Remove top pan and set aside off heat.

title: cindy's fudge
directions: Boil on high heat until sugar, milk, vanilla and butter comes to a boil, then turn heat halfway and boil another 3 minutes. Remove from heat; add 1 1/2 cups peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch buttered cake pan.

title: snack
directions: Heat oil.
Add seasonings.
Pour over crackers and Cheerios; stir well.
Put on sheet; stir well.
Put into warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried bread
directions: Flatten each roll to a 3 1/2-inch diameter.
Place a few at a time in deep hot oil (375°).
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; stir well.
Gently toss fried bread in sugar mixture. Serve immediately.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: cabbage apple slaw
directions: Prepare Orange Salad Dressing (recipe follows).
Put plumped dark seedless raisins into a bowl and pour in dressing to cover. Chill raisins and remaining dressing.
In a salad bowl, toss desired amount of shredded carrots and cabbage with the marinated raisins and dressing to coat.

title: ham and potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes, ham, onion, egg, parsley and marjoram; mix well.
Shape into 4 to 6 cakes.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Melt butter in a frying pan.
Brown cakes in butter.
Serve with scrambled eggs.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Crumble Ritz crackers on top. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except potatoes.
Pour over potatoes and mix again.
Heat in double boiler.
Serve hot, garnished with salad greens.

title: easy italian cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg yolks, butter, buttermilk and vanilla with mixer.
Fold in coconut, pecans and stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: green bean italian
directions: Place the beans in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Heat in the microwave, covered, for six minutes.
Add the onion and Italian dressing. Heat on full power for four minutes.
Serve hot topped with crumbled bacon.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together twice flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut shortening into flour.
Combine buttermilk and light corn syrup.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead lightly with finger tips.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.

title: fried fudge candy
directions: This takes stirring continuously very hard.
Not easy to make, but the effort is well worth it.
Melt 1 cup of sugar.
Add 1/2 can of Carnation
milk.
Stir until melted.
Add another cup of sugar.
Stir until melted.
Add rest of the milk.
Stir well.
Add last cup of sugar and stir to soft ball stage.
Beat and add vanilla and nuts last.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.
It's best to use large, iron skillet, if you have one.

title: cherry tortilla
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together butter, water and sugar. Butter dish.
Layer tortilla flat; put 1 spoonful of pie filling in middle and roll up.
Repeat.
When finished, pour sugar mixture over tortillas and bake until golden brown.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325.
In oven, melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Tilt dish to coat bottom.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, salt and milk until well blended.
Stir in onion, and pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set but still moist, about 35 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven just long enough to melt cheese.
Serves about 12.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Boil until thick flour and milk; stir while cooking.
Mix, then add remaining ingredients and beat vigorously.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning with electric mixer until well blended.
Spread mixture on large serving platter.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomato and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: lemony light cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda and sliced fruit.
Serve over ice.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter, saute onions and mushrooms.
Add water, consomme, salt and pepper (to taste).
Pour rice into mixture and stir. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not stir.

title: milky way homemade ice cream
directions: Combine condensed milk and Milky Way bars in bowl. Melt in microwave until all big chunks are gone. Pour enough milk in mixture to stir. Pour mixture in freezer. Add syrup. Pour in milk to fill line. Freeze.

title: fried squirrel
directions: Mix salt and pepper with flour in brown paper bag.
Shake pieces of squirrel in flour mixture and brown in melted shortening in a heavy skillet. Lower heat after browning and cover the skillet tightly.
Cook over low heat for 1/2 to 1 hour or until well done.
Remove cover during the last 10 minutes to crisp outer surface.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and add nuts.
Bake at 380° for about 50 minutes.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loaves.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Put half of cheese in greased 2 or 3-quart casserole.
Combine sausage, sour cream, dry mustard, paprika and salt.
Spread over grated cheese.
(This can be done a day ahead.)
Beat eggs and pour over sausage mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes (until brown on edges and eggs are set).
Serves 10 to 12.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Stir sugar into cabbage.
Place half of cabbage into large bowl.
Cover with chopped onions.
Top with remaining cabbage. Pour boiling Hot Dressing over slowly.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate at once.
Chill 24 hours.
Stir well before serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Can use sugar-free hot cocoa mix and artificial sweetener for a sugar-free mix.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make cake according to box. After cake is done, punch holes in it and pour Eagle Brand and cream of coconut over it while still hot. Let cool. Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip. Refrigerate afterward. Let set overnight.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Mix soda in milk. Stir into mixture.
Add bananas.
Add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 40 minutes.

title: layered walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Chop nuts fine.
Soften gelatin in water in pan.
Stir in pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, lightly beaten egg yolks, spice and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Turn heat very low; cook for 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove.
Add vanilla; cool.
Chill until thickens slightly.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in 2 tablespoons sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold into mixture, along with nuts.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake and bake according to directions.
While hot after baked, poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour condensed milk over cake; let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle coconut on cake.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot or lime jello salad mold
directions: Mix dry jello with cream cheese.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water and stir until all lumps are gone.
Add pineapple and stir.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: ropa vieja
directions: In a pot large enough to hold the beef; bring stock, water, peppercorns, garlic, and bay leaves to a boil.
Add beef and return to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.
Remove from heat and cool in broth.
When cool enough, shred the meat with your fingers.

title: brigadeiros(candy from brazil)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine condensed milk, cocoa powder and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 5 minutes or until mixture forms a ball around the spoon and pulls away from sides of pan.
Turn mixture out onto buttered plate to cool.
When cool enough to handle, butter hands and form mixture into one-inch balls.
Roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chocolate nuggets
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Add nuts and noodles. Mix together.
Drop from teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand 2 hours or refrigerate.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with soft bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: johnny cakes
directions: Combine egg, sugar and 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon butter flavor Crisco in medium bowls.
Stir in sour milk and baking soda. Add flour, cornmeal and salt.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cover.
Let stand in cool place for 30 minutes. Pour remaining shortening on griddle or in large skillet.
Heat on medium heat.
Spoon tablespoonfuls of batter onto griddle.
Brown on one side.
Turn.
Brown on other side.
Serve with syrup, jam or honey.
Makes 18 Johnny Cakes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Marinate all ingredients at least 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and bake sweet potatoes at 375 degree oven for 50 minutes or until tender.
Let potatoes cool.
While potatoes are baking dice and brown bacon.
When bacon is brown, add onions and cook tender.
Remove to strainer and strain bacon grease.
Press mixture gently.
Lay potatoes on side.
Slice 1/2 inch off top. Remove pulp from top and inside potato, leaving 1/4 inch thick wall.
Combine pulp, sour cream and butter.
Mash with potato masher.
Add bacon, onion, salt and nutmeg.
Stuff potato. Sprinkle with pecans.
Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Roll crackers.
Chop other ingredients and mix together. Moisten with cream and form into a roll.
Put in refrigerator. Serve with whipped cream.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 3 to 4 hours. Roll into 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Frost and decorate with sprinkles or whatever.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Put pineapple with juice in double boiler and bring to boil. Add jello and dissolve.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Beat on low speed with mixer until mixed well.
Pour in dish and refrigerate.

title: dill onion vinaigrette
directions: Combine ingredients in jar.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Chill to blend flavors.
Shake again before serving with mixed garden salads.

title: ratatouille a la greque
directions: Combine eggplant, onion and garlic in a 3-quart casserole. Drizzle with olive oil.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Stir in zucchini, bell pepper and basil.
Re-cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, re-cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cheese, black pepper and salt; serve immediately.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly each time.
Add all dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake in a well-floured, well-greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter. Stir in sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add buttermilk and vanilla. Blend well and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Mix flour or cornmeal with salt and pepper.
Coat tomatoes with this mixture.
Place in heavy skillet containing hot shortening.
Fry slowly until brown, turning once.
Do not burn.

title: rosemary's beef brisket
directions: Sear beef in frying pan, then put in baking dish.
Add hot water, Tabasco, garlic and Kitchen Bouquet.
Cover meat with onions.
Cover baking dish and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Can let cool and slice, then reheat to serve; also freezes well.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken pieces.
Remove skin and bones and cut meat into chunks.
Prepare broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of 12 x 7-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
In medium bowl, mix next 3 ingredients together well and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix butter with bread crumbs and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until cheese and crumbs start to bubble and brown.
You may make ahead of time and refrigerate, but let it come to room temperature before cooking.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, and food coloring until well mixed.
In a separate bowl sift flour, salt, soda, and cocoa.
Add flour mixture alternating with buttermilk and beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Bake in three 8-inch greased pans or one 9 x 13 inch pan for 35-40 minutes at 350°.

title: pink lemonade
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a glass jar or a large vacuum bottle.
Cover and shake until the sugar is dissolved.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Three hours before eating, put shrimp in bowl.
Mix all ingredients.
Arrange evenly in shallow pan; cover and let set at room temperature for 2 hours.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Stir and broil 5 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O into Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Drain pineapple and oranges (cut oranges into pieces) and stir into Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese and mix thoroughly.
Fold in marshmallows.
Refrigerate until served.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruity cranberry bread
directions: Sift
together
flour,
soda, cream of tartar and salt. Beat shortening
until
creamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light
and
fluffy.
Add
eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, 1/4 at a time, stirring only until flour
is
moistened.
Very carefully fold in cranberry sauce cubes
and
chopped nuts.
Turn into a well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5
x 3-inch) and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.
Also makes 4 mini loaves.

title: diabetic coke salad
directions: Bring cherries and water to boil in a saucepan.
Add cherry jello, stirring until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add cola and pineapple.
Pour into glass serving bowl.
Chill for 4 to 5 hours, until firm.
Yields 10 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water; place in bag and shake.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn once.

title: chicken lynn casserole
directions: Stew chicken and bone; cut into large chunks.
Put in a greased casserole.
Mix together soup and some stew juice.
Cream soup and 1/4 cup chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter.
Mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top, then sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: joyce's banana pudding
directions: Cream the cream cheese, then add condensed milk.
Pour instant dry pudding mix in this.
Add Cool Whip.
Add milk; mix well. Layer wafers, bananas, then the mix.
Keep layering until you have used all the mix.

title: irish chicken
directions: Cut up chicken, onion and celery into chunks.
Cook onion, celery and chicken chunks until chicken is done.
Add 3/4 cup catsup and 1 cup water; mix all together.
Add flour until mixture thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 395°.
Potatoes must be hot!
Use mixer to blend all ingredients into potatoes.
Place into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 35 minutes or until edges brown lightly.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil and dry ingredients together.
Pour over crackers and stir until well coated.

title: all in one quiche
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in blender and mix well.
Turn into ungreased deep 9-inch or regular 10-inch pie plate.
Add meat or shellfish, poking into batter.
Top with onions, mushrooms and cheese.
Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in oleo for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over; do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 450°.

title: cheesy chicken roll
directions: Separate rolls and roll out, then put a heaping teaspoon of chicken on each roll and place 1/2 slice of cheese on top of chicken.
Roll this up and put in baking dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 or 40 minutes.
Serve a little of the sauce over each roll.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; heat over low heat, stirring constantly until piping hot.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine the ingredients in a saucepan and heat for about 10 minutes or until all ingredients are well blended.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and cook 12 to 14 minutes. Drain meat mixture.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix flour (or cornstarch) with sugar and cocoa.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes or until set.

title: "philly" 15 minute cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons of sugar and 3 tablespoons of melted butter into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots for 30 minutes; drain.
Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together and add chopped nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan or 2 pound coffee can.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: becky's chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into canister.
Finish filling canister to fill line with homogenized milk.

title: honolulu burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, eggs, onion, steak sauce, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into 8 patties at least as large as pineapple slices.
Grill patties on barbecue grill.
After first side is cooked, turn, place 1 pineapple slice on each burger and top each with one slice of cheese.
Finish cooking.
Serve on buns. Makes eight 1/4-pound burgers.

title: cool rise - rapid mix rolls
directions: With a mixer, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add margarine and hot water and mix for 2 minutes at medium speed. Add egg and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Using spoon, add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Cover for 20 minutes.
Shape into rolls or place in loaf pan.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Dough may be refrigerated for up to 48 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water;
set
aside.
Mix dry ingredients
in order given.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients. Stir in buttermilk and yeast.
Blend thoroughly.
Knead lightly. Roll it out on a floured board and cut out biscuits. Place on greased pan and let them rise slightly.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: raw relish
directions: Grind vegetables.
Put with salt and stir.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Squeeze out juice.
Mix vinegar and sugar.
Mix with vegetables.
Put in jars and seal.

title: "fish" cakes and sauce
directions: Grind soyameat, celery and onion.
Combine all other ingredients.
If too moist, thicken with crumbs.
Form into patties and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 9.
Serve with sauce.

title: black pepper london broil
directions: Wipe steak with damp cloth and pierce each side with a fork. Rub each side with 1 1/4 teaspoons tenderizer and 1 1/2 teaspoons pepper.
Heat butter and oil in large black skillet.
Add steak and cook each side 12 to 15 minutes for rare, longer for medium. Remove meat and add stock.
Heat about 2 minutes.
Serve over meat.

title: peanut butter cup cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with brown sugar and vanilla until light. Add peanut butter and mix thoroughly. Beat eggs until light and add to creamed mixture.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Squish up with hands until mixed.
Mold into 1 loaf or 2 small loaves.
Place in greased pan. Top with bacon strips.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend all together and serve with raw veggies.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar and lemon juice until thick.
Cool.
Add cream to egg mixture.
Add fruit, cherries and marshmallows. Refrigerate.
Yield:
1 quart.
Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 2 g, fat 7 g, calories 131.
One serving (1/2 cup) = 1 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 1/2 fat exchange.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with pecans and coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour over nuts and coconut.

title: chocolate chip tassies
directions: For topping mixture, cream together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Blend and set aside.
In mixing bowl, sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, 1/2 teaspoon salt and soda.
Add water, oil and vanilla. Mix well.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Heat bean dip and seasonings.
When steaming hot, add cheese. Stir until melted.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: lomi lomi poke
directions: Cut
fish
into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients, including
fish,
in large bowl with your hands.
If you want, limu may also be added.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with cut up onion and green pepper, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain.
Cook spaghetti.
Add Ragu and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix together.
Put Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° to 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: barbecued hamburger for 50 people
directions: Brown meat, peppers, onions and celery.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook gently for 1 hour.
Serve on split hamburger buns (warmed in oven).
This freezes well.

title: dennis walker's irish soda bread
directions: Mix together the raisins, sour cream and eggs.
To this mixture add the sugar, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Divide batter into two greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Place on lower shelf of a 350° oven for 30 minutes, then place on higher shelf for remaining 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Test with a toothpick.
(I substitute light sour cream and egg substitute.)
Makes 2 loaves.

title: orange balls
directions: Thaw but do not dilute orange juice. Combine remaining ingredients with orange juice and let set 5 minutes.
Form into small ball and roll in additional powdered sugar. No baking.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine hash brown potatoes, onion, celery, carrots, water and chicken broth in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: better tastin' green beans
directions: Fill a large saucepan 1/4 full with water.
Add green beans, onion, bacon, vegetable seasoning blend and lemon pepper.
Cover. Cook on medium-low heat until tender.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, zucchini, and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, and pecans. Combine mixtures.
Pour into 3 small greased and floured bread tins.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: quick cookies
directions: Wash your hands.
Measure peanut butter, honey and coconut into bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Measure and stir in 1/2 cup cereal. Spread the rest of cereal on wax paper (3/4 cup).
Make balls of mixture with fingertips and roll in cereal.
Chill until firm.

title: peppered cocktail snacks
directions: Mix when sausage and cheese are at room temperature.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
May be frozen before baking.
Take out as needed and bake at 400°.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into large salad bowl.
Douse with lemon juice.
Marinate in refrigerator, then serve.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown in skillet.
Arrange in baking dish.
Rinse pan with 1/2 cup water.
Pour pan juices over meat.
Slice potatoes and carrots over meat.
Sprinkle in onion. Spread soup over top.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven covered with foil.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and add seasoning and simmer.
Fill tortillas with ground beef.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with following:
Mix chili, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over tortillas, spreading sauce over all tops.
Cover with grated cheese (if desired).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mush
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and add boiling water.
Cook 5 minutes.
In the meantime, fry sausage.
Press out grease.
Add brown sugar to mush along with the sausage, stirring well until blended.
When cold, slice and fry.
Good with syrup or eggs.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip, then add sour cream. Stir gently.
Place vanilla wafers and bananas in layers as you would when making a regular banana pudding.
Top off with crushed wafers and refrigerate until ready to serve after adding pudding mixture.
You may also seal top with whipped cream.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.

Pour 2/3 of the batter in Bundt pan. Add the brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Sprinkle over filling well and add remaining batter. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or when springs back when touched lightly.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear the lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with the torn lettuce.
Layer the next four ingredients on top of the lettuce.
Blend the sugar into the mayonnaise.
Spread the mixture evenly over the top of the layered vegetables.
Sprinkle the crumbled bacon and the Cheddar cheese on top of the mayonnaise.
Cover the pan and refrigerate for several hours before serving.
(You may use imitation bacon bits instead of bacon.)

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Stir in thawed berries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cover bottom of 9-inch pan with half the torn angel food pieces; pour half of the strawberries and cream mixture over the cake; make another layer of rest of torn cake.
Pour remaining strawberry mix over this.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours to set.
Cut into squares.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Chill, tightly covered, for at least one hour.
Serve over lettuce leaf and garnish with mint or parsley.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Drizzle over the top 1 stick of melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, layer in order turkey, onions, rice and cabbage.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts with sour cream
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in a skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, tarragon and pepper.
Spread chicken breasts with mixture and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add shortening and cream.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix salt with flour.
Add to butter and sugar mixture alternating with milk.
Add flouring.
Bake at 325° for an hour and a half.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp and tear up.
Beat cheese, onions, lemon juice, salt, pepper, Tabasco, garlic salt and Worcestershire, adding mayonnaise.
Fold in shrimp.
Keep cold and serve with chips.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add carrots, nuts and eggs; mix well.
Place mixture in a greased or oiled loaf pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fried potato cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients together in mixing bowl. Cover bottom of nonstick frying pan with oil.
Put large tablespoonful of potato mix in pan (like a pancake). Cook over medium heat until brown on each side.
Make sure pan is very hot when you add mixture.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice and water to a boil.
Cover and let set for 30 minutes.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add milk and stir.
Pour rice in 1 3/4-quart greased casserole.
Pour the custard (liquid) over the rice.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake about 1 1/4 hours (350°) in a pan of hot water.
Pudding is done when inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 325° until filling is firm in middle.

title: oatmeal chewies
directions: Combine oats and sugar with oil.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add egg, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet and bake in 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lizzie's baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente.
Combine tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper and sugar.
In greased casserole put layer of spaghetti, tomatoes and cheese and continue with layers, ending with cheese. Bake 1/2 hour or until cheese melts at 350°.
Stir twice during baking to keep moist.

title: mom's artichoke dip
directions: Using a food processor, mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with nacho chips or crackers.

title: canning green beans
directions: String and break green beans.
Wash and put in clean jars. Cover beans with cold water and put lids on tight.
Put in pressure canner and put water around jars.
Place lid on canner and place on stove on medium heat.
When canner reaches 10 pounds pressure, cook for 10 to 11 minutes and turn off.
Let
cool and remove.

title: california roast beef
directions: Place steak in a baking dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) over steak.
Sprinkle powdered onion soup on top. Cover entire baking dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Mix mushroom soup, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup grated cheese, eggs and onion.
Fold broccoli into mixture and top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 package enchilada mix. Stir.
Cut up tortillas into 1-inch pieces.
Add to meat.
Pour in milk and soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour everything into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top casserole with 2 cups shredded cheese last 5 minutes of baking.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: olive dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn; make 12
cups.
Place in large bowl.	Combine sugars, corn syrup, water, vinegar,
salt
and soda in 2 quart saucepan.
Heat to	boiling
over
medium-high
heat, stirring constantly.
Cook at 260°
on
a
candy
thermometer
or until small amount of mixture dropped
into
very cold water forms a hard ball.	Reduce heat to	low.
Stir in butter until melted. Pour syrup in thin streams	over
corn in bowl, stirring until corn is coated.
Cool
slightly.
Butter
hands and shape into 3-inch balls.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half. Stir until thickened.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Stir until smooth. Fold in crab legs and/or shrimp.
Heat 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter or margarine, sugars and vanilla pudding.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Can use chocolate pudding to make it double chocolate.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Whisk together eggs, yogurt and butter in a medium bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix until just well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch heavy skillet and bake 40 minutes.

title: lime cheese salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice with enough water to make 1 cup. Bring to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot juice; cool.
Mash cream cheese and add to gelatin.
Let set slightly.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in mold and chill until firm.

title: will's peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Mix peanut butter and jelly with a spoon in a bowl. Get a knife and get the peanut butter and jelly out and put it on the bread. If you like, you can pour ketchup on it.

title: acapulco enchiladas
directions: Combine
chicken,
olives,
almonds and enough sauce to moisten
(about 1/3 cup); set aside.
Fry tortillas in oil and dip into heated enchilada sauce.
Evenly spoon chicken mixture down center
of	each
tortilla	and
roll to enclose.
Place enchiladas,
seam
side
down in shallow ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking
dish.
Top	with
remaining
sauce	and
sprinkle with cheese.
Bake
uncovered
in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through.
Mix sour cream with onion and serve cold to	spoon over.
Makes 12 enchiladas (about 4 to 6 servings).

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil until soft.
Add tomato paste mixed with water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour. Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix cottage cheese, macaroni and sauce in large casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until the cheese is all melted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground beef; drain grease.
Mix tomato sauce with water and enchilada seasoning, stir into meat and simmer 2 or 3 minutes. Layer bowl with chips, pour half of meat mixture over chips. Pour rest of sauce, sprinkle cheese.
If cheese doesn't melt, either put in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with remaining chips.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a 12 inch skillet over medium heat, saute meat and onions in 2 Tbsp. margarine until browned. Season with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Stir in soup and 1 c. of beef broth (reserving 1/4 c.). Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add mushrooms. Blend remaining 1/4 c. of beef broth with flour. Stir into meat mixture; cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Add sour cream and heat through. DO NOT BOIL. Serve over hot egg noodles.

title: chicken saute
directions: Slice chicken breasts into 1-inch strips.
Dust with flour on all sides.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute strips while adding rest of ingredients.
Put lid on and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add finely chopped onion and cook until onion is clear.
Add 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil. Add crawfish tails and shallots.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soup and 1/4 of the cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Take cheese slices and place over Tater Tots. Bake until potatoes are brown and cheese has melted.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Make cake according to package directions, except use a large pan (10 1/2 x 14 1/2) or equivalent cake pan for a thinner cake. After the cake is done, cool thoroughly. Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip. Smooth on top of cake. Next, mix glaze with strawberries. Top cake with this and chill overnight.

title: dutch apple squares
directions: Combine apples, condensed milk and cinnamon.
In bowl, combine 1 cup biscuit mix and 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir into sliced apples.
In another bowl, combine rest of biscuit mix and 2 tablespoons butter and brown sugar.
Spread over apple mix in baking dish.
Bake until top is brown and apples are done.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pasta-in-a-pot
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown; drain excess grease. Add spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and drained mushrooms; mix well.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni until done; drain and rinse in cold water.
In a large casserole dish, pour half of the macaroni shells.
Cover shells with half of the sauce-meat mixture.
Spread half of the sour cream over the sauce-meat mixture and top with layers of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat this process with the remainder of the macaroni shells, meat sauce, sour cream and Mozzarella slices.
Place cover on casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: flan
directions: Caramelize cup of sugar.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Roll dish to cover sides.
Pour in custard mixture: milk, water, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Place in pan of water, at least 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nacho dip
directions: You can use small diced onion, 1 can chopped green chilies and 2 diced tomatoes if you DO NOT use the salsa.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: gourmet chicken salad
directions: Mix all salad ingredients together.

title: easy pork barbecue
directions: For 6 servings you will need:

title: potato dumplings
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender. Drain well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Peel and grated potatoes.

title: nana's chili or spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in enough fat to keep from sticking.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain.
Add seasonings and 2 cans of water.
Stir well and cook over low heat for approximately 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
If chili or spaghetti thickens too much, add more water.
If making chili add beans.

title: dilled cucumber and tomato salad
directions: Place cucumbers in shallow container.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a small jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously. Pour marinade over cucumber and chill 6 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, slice tomatoes.
Remove cucumber from marinade. Arrange alternating slices on lettuce.

title: baked date pudding
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in hot water in pan which pudding is to be baked.
Pour into syrup mixture the remaining ingredients. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serve cooled with whipped cream.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix grape jello with hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Let congeal in refrigerator.

title: fish and vegetable skillet dinner
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Stir in salt, dill, pepper and lemon juice.
Add carrots, potatoes and onion.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat.
Stir occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender (9 to 12 minutes).
Add fish.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato until heated through and fish flakes.

title: quick and easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Do not add water; this makes a very good night snack.
Take if from the experts.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish and top with 3 uncooked bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast mandalay
directions: Coat chicken breasts in mixture of flour, curry powder and salt (if desired).
Brown lightly in oil.
Place chicken in large baking dish.
Stir sugar, bouillon, onion, water, apricots, lemon and soy sauce into frypan drippings.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until tender. Move chicken breasts to serving platter.
Add cornstarch to sauce until desired thickness is reached.
Pour over chicken and top with canned apricots.

title: spinach salad dip
directions: Boil spinach; cut up more.
Drain very, very well.
Combine in bowl with sour cream and spinach as needed.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cut hole in bread round and fill with dip.

title: hot rice
directions: Cook tomatoes 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions, chopped and sauteed in oil, red pepper, paprika, sugar and salt.
Cook rice as directed; let cool 5 minutes.
Add rice to tomato mixture and cook 20 minutes longer.
Pack in hot jars and cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Blend sugar, flour, pineapple juice, beaten eggs, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Cook 3 quarts water, oil, salt, and acini de pepe.
Drain and rinse.
Add cooled custard to pasta.
Mix and refrigerate overnight in an airtight container. Add oranges, pineapple chunks, crushed pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut and marshmallows.

title: chicken margaretta(chicken and rice)
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Dot with butter on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: lemon-zucchini cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg and lemon rind, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in zucchini and walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks.
Combine 10x sugar and lemon juice; stir well. Drizzle over warm cookies; let cool completely.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: turkey breast roasted in bag
directions: Shake flour in a plastic browning or roasting bag (14 x 20-inches) and place in a roasting pan, 2-inches deep.
Spread onion, celery and carrot in bag.
Rinse turkey breast and pat dry. Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and herb blend.
Place turkey on top of vegetables.
Close bag with a twist tie and make six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag with tip of sharp knife.

title: calzones with pasta sauce
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients until blended. Stir in pepperoni and chopped cheese slices. Divide each pizza crust into 2 portions. Roll each dough portion into a 7-inch circle. Spoon 1/2 cup cottage cheese mixture in center of each circle. Fold dough over filling, pressing edges to seal; place on a lightly greased aluminum foil-lined baking sheet. Prick dough several times with a fork. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden. Let stand 5 minutes. Serve calzones with warm pasta sauce. Yield: 4 servings. Prep: 25 minutes. Bake: 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine xx sugar and peanut butter; blend until appearance of biscuit mix.
Spread on pie shell.

title: jellied chicken salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup
cold water.	Dissolve in hot broth. Add lemon juice and
salt.
Chill until partially set. Stir in remaining ingredients;
pour
into	5 to 12 individual molds or 5 1/2-cup ring mold.	Mold
until firm.
Unmold; pass mayonnaise.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine in pan on stove.
Stir in sugar.
Stir in cocoa.
Add evaporated milk and stir.
Bring to a full boil and stir continually for 1 minute.
Take off stove and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Serve over ice cream.

title: ro-tel corn
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add corn and Ro-Tel. Simmer for at least 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut vegetables into pieces.
Place chicken, carrots, celery, onion, potatoes and seasoning in pot and add enough water to cover.
Boil until tender.
Debone chicken.
Line a casserole dish with pie crust.
Put chicken and vegetables in the casserole dish. Combine soup, broth and cornstarch.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with bread, bread crumbs or pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy walnuts
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Heat walnuts in moderate oven (375°) for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Combine sugar, water, salt and cinnamon in heavy saucepan.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook, without stirring, to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat by hand for 1 minute or until mixture begins to get creamy.
Add vanilla and warm walnuts.
Stir gently, until nuts are well coated.
Turn out on waxed paper; separate with a fork.

title: sausage and grits breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine hot grits, cheese and butter; stir until cheese and butter melt.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into grits. Pour into casserole over sausage.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
This casserole may be made the night before, refrigerated and baked the next day.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in small baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: salsa
directions: Except for avocado, mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Let it stand at room temperature for about an hour.
Stir several times, then add avocado right before serving with tortilla chips.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Melt margarine and add last.
Pour in uncooked pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except Cool Whip), adding nuts last.
Grease generously a pizza pan or dish.
Spread mixture within 1-inch of each side of pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Cool and top with Cool Whip.
Top this with any fresh fruit.

title: nacho chip dip
directions: Layer ingredients in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer as listed.

title: tuna a'la ed
directions: Flake fish with fork. Add celery, onion and parsley.
Combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice, mustard, wine and pepper sauce and Old Bay.
Mix with fish until evenly distributed and well moistened.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except nuts and white chocolate, together at medium speed of beater.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Continue mixing until well blended.
Fold in Macadamia nuts and white chocolate pieces.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep dish.
Mix dry ingredients and add milk. Pour batter over melted butter.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling. Bake in oven at 375°.
Other fruits may be used.
When baked, the crust is on the top.

title: baked denver sandwich
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Arrange 4 slices, buttered side down, in 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, ham, green pepper and onion.
Place remaining slices, buttered side up, on top of filling.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and cayenne pepper. Pour over sandwiches in pan.
Press each down with pancake turner to blend egg mixture in bread.
If desired, cover and refrigerate as long as overnight; or bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes until sandwiches feel firm to the touch and egg mixture is set.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Fry the ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain the grease from the meat.
Add the salt and pepper.
Cut up the bell pepper into small pieces.
Cut up 1/2 onion in small pieces, then cut 2 small tomatoes, sliced small.
Pour the tomato paste over all ingredients.
Mix together, then let the ingredients cook for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour. Add milk. Cook 2 minutes. Add cheese; stir until melted. Season to taste. Add onion. Place a layer of diced potatoes in a buttered baking dish, then layer of sauce. Repeat alternately with sauce on top. Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: black bottoms
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar, egg and salt in first bowl.
Add chocolate chips.

title: raisin cake
directions: Bring all to a boil for 3 minutes; let cool.
Add 2 cups flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon soda and nuts.
Mix well. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Her mother's recipe.

title: buttermilk pound cake(this is a very moist cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs.
Cream for 10 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Add buttermilk, salt and soda. Alternate a little at a time with vanilla and flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done to touch in loaf pans that have been oiled real good.
When done, turn upside-down on sheet pan.
It will drop from pan when it is cooled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Save the broth.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into florets and blanch (8 to 10 minutes) in boiling water.
Drain and transfer to buttered baking dish.
In another bowl mix cream, egg yolks, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, cayenne and cheese together.
Place sauce over cauliflower in casserole and coat evenly.
Melt butter and mix in crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add butter.
Let stand until butter is melted.
Add celery soup, cheese and mexicorn. Save a little cheese for top.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine; cook 12 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream; stir.
Cool and slice.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat fat in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper and meat.
Cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer about an hour.

title: cage bach(welsh cakes)
directions: Rub flour, butter and sugar to fine crumbs.
Add spice.
Make a well in the center, then add egg and fruit.
Mix to a firm dough. Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut into rounds. Cook on a heated griddle or heavy frying pan until brown on both sides. Cool and spread with butter before eating.

title: peanut butter fudge recipe 1
directions: Cook sugar and evaporated milk to soft ball stage (235°F). Stir while cooking. Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme or marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Cool.

title: lemonade ice cream
directions: Thaw and dilute lemonade as directed on can.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour mixture into a freezer can of a one gallon electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturers instructions.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and shortening.
In another bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Beat eggs and add to yeast mixture.
Pour potato water into first ingredients.
Add salt, then flour; knead and set in icebox to rise to double in size.
Put dough on floured board; cut each roll from dough and work with fingers.
Roll over in greased pan.
Let rolls rise to twice their size and bake in moderate oven, 400°, until brown or about 30 minutes.

title: amanda's favorite kidney bean salad
directions: Chop onion fine.
Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients until crumbly.
Beat 1 egg in measuring cup and finish filling cup with cold water.
Pour over crumbly mixture and mix well.
This dough will keep in refrigerator indefinitely or you can freeze.
(For flaky crust, use ice water.)

title: peach upside-down pudding cake
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange peaches over sugar mixture.
Combine all remainder ingredients in large bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Spoon carefully into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Invert to platter; remove pan. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: white brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Add eggs, then vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put 8 to 10 chicken breasts or pieces in a shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Turn chicken over halfway through cooking and baste. Serve over white rice.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Place in 8 x 8 dish.
Add undiluted soups.
Mix salt and pepper and top with Crispy Crowns (large Tater Tots).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Line and grease 5 (9-inch) spring-form pans.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups of cookie crumbs per cheesecake over the bottom of each pan. Combine cream cheese and sugar in a large mixer; beat until smooth.
Add the pumpkin; continue to beat.
Add the spices; mix well.
Scrape the sides of the bowl with a spatula.
Add eggs slowly, one at a time; beat in cream.
Divide evenly among the pans.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Rotate pans in the oven every 30 minutes for even heat distribution.

title: luncheon chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken,
celery,
fruits and nuts.
Blend oil, orange juice, vinegar and seasonings.
Add to chicken mixture. Let stand for 1
hour.
Drain.
Add mayonnaise and toss lightly.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Line a large pie pan with rolls.
Spread with mustard.
Simmer with oleo until soft and transparent, zucchini and onions.
Add spices.
Beat eggs and mix with cheese.
Pour zucchini mixture into eggs and cheese and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: korozott hungarian cheese spread
directions: Mix well and spread on small pieces of bread or crackers. Garnish with sliced olives or squares of green pepper.
If preferred, use cottage cheese instead of cream cheese.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla, coconut and buttermilk.
Pour in 3 unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: turnip saute
directions: In saucepan, bring 1-inch of water to a boil.
Add turnips; cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Saute carrots and onion in oleo until tender.
Stir in turnips, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook, turning frequently, to well heated, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place a layer of the cheese, onion and broccoli in a serving dish.
Repeat three times.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll into a ball.
You can roll in chili powder if you want to.
Then roll into crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place the broccoli, cauliflower, garbanzo beans and onions in a bowl. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese together well. Pour into vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Mix cocoa and boiling water; add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add margarine.
Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Combine milk and vanilla; add alternately to dry ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fudgy oatmeal squares
directions: Stir oats and water together.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in a sifter.
Mix shortening, oatmeal mixture and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix at low speed for 3 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
Serve.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Cut steak into
thin
strips, slicing slightly diagonal from top to bottom.
Combine
remaining
ingredients and marinate steak for about 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Weave meat onto small skewers.
Grill about 2 minutes on each side.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown
beef,
pour off fat.
Add celery, pepper (green), onion,
salt
and
pepper.	Put in greased casserole dish.	Mix milk,
eggs
and
Bisquick; beat until smooth.
Pour over beef. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in all other ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Makes one 9 x 13-inch or two 8-inch square cakes.
Line pan with waxed paper and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, then increase to 375° for 10 minutes to brown top.

title: no name pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together and add eggs and butter; mix well.
Add walnuts, chocolate and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: maple pecan ring(makes 2 coffee cakes)
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Add margarine.
Gradually add hot water.
Stir fast and well.
At this point add eggs and 1/2 cup flour, stir or beat well.
Now stir in 3 to 4 more cups of flour.
Make a soft dough.
Knead dough on a floured board about 10 minutes, then cover dough with plastic wrap and let sit for 1/2 hour.
Meanwhile, combine pecans, brown sugar and maple flavoring.
Push in the dough and divide in 1/2.
On a floured board, roll 1/2 the dough into a 16 x 8-inch rectangle. Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle 1/2 of the sugar mix on the dough.
Roll up dough from the long side to form a 16-inch roll.
Pinch seams to seal.
Place the sealed edge down in a circle on greased baking sheet.
Seal ends together firmly.
Cut 2/3 of the way into ring with scissors at 1-inch intervals. Repeat with remaining dough and brown sugar mixture.
Brush rings with oil and cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.

title: crunchy chicken crescents
directions: *May use plain cream cheese plus 1 tablespoon chopped chives.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next five ingredients.
Stir in pecans and pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: deer steak
directions: Cover steak with water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until meat is tender.
More liquid can be added.
Sometimes add 2 cans tomatoes for different flavor.

title: onion pie
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with the crackers. Pour the 1/2 cup melted oleo over the top.
(I cup down on this amount of oleo.)
Saute the onions in 1/4 cup oleo.
(I used less oleo and added water.)
Cook until tender. Arrange over crust. Sprinkle the cheese over top of the onions.
Beat the eggs. Add the milk and pour over top. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: post toasties bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and Post Toasties.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan or drop by spoon.
Cool.

title: beef roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over roast.
Bake until tender.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Heat 1 cup cranberry juice.
Dissolve jello in hot juice.
Add remaining juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour in mold; chill until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well.
Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Peel the stems and cut in small pieces.
Blanch quickly in salted, boiling water. Drain quickly and run cold water to stop cooking process.
Mix all together and put into a tightly covered dish overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles; drain.
In a large pan, spread enough sauce to cover bottom of pan (4 cups).
Then alternate layer of noodles, cheese, sauce, noodles, etc.
Use 3 layers of noodles.
End with meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients and mix until creamy.
Add flour, orange juice and extract and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip-orange zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar and continue beating until well blended.
Stir in oil, vanilla, zucchini, nuts, chocolate chips and orange rind.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir into egg mixture.
Turn into 2 greased 9 X 5 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Remove from pans; cool on rack.
Chill before slicing.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: manicotti kirkpatrick
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil Pam.
Add next 6 ingredients and cook 10 minutes.
Cook 20 manicotti noodles according to package directions.
Stuff with spinach mixture and make a single layer in baking dish.
Cover layer with sauce. Bake, covered, about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over stuffed noodles and bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: guacamole
directions: Place peeled and seeded avocados in a bowl.
Mash with a fork and add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: In a large frying pan saute onions, green peppers and mushrooms with margarine for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
In another bowl, beat eggs, milk, and pepper.
Add to frying pan. Stir in
the potatoes, then add ham, and 1/2 c. cheese. Cook until eggs are almost set.
Then add 1 1/2 c. cheese, let stand covered for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted and eggs are set.
tags: loose packed frozen hash brown potatoes

title: cowboy steak 'n veggie soup
directions: Cut beef into 1/4 inch thick strips, cut each strip into pieces.
In medium bowl combine beef, basil, pepper, garlic and oil.
Toss to coat.

title: teriyaki beef broil
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across grain into 1/4 inch strips.
Place steak in shallow container.
Combine soy sauce and remaining ingredients; pour over steak.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake and bake by directions on box in three 8-inch cake pans.
While hot, punch cake with fork; do not punch to bottom of pan.
Mix milk and sugar to dissolve just to boiling point.
Pour mixture on cake top.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix coconut and Cool Whip; frost cake.
Save enough coconut for top.
Wrap cake in plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze.

title: stars and stripes toast
directions: Toast bread.
Cool a few minutes.
Cut off crusts; spread about 1 tablespoon of cream cheese.
Put 3 berries from the jam in a row, then put 3 more in a row under the first.
Make a thin row of jam.
Leave white spaces between the rows.
You'll end up with about 4 or 5 rows on the toast.
Makes 1 piece of Stars and Stripes toast.

title: fruit soup
directions: Mix together the tapioca, sugar, salt and 1 cup water. Add the remaining 1/2 cup water and the orange juice concentrate.
Use over fruit.

title: "chill out" chili
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic in oil in large saucepan, stirring frequently, just until meat loses its pink color (10 minutes). Sprinkle chili powder, cumin, oregano and salt over meat; mix well to coat ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except toppings; mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into bowls; top with sour cream or chopped green onions.
Good with crusty cornbread!

title: m&m rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter on low heat in
a large saucepan.
Add marshmallows and melt on low heat (while stirring). When they are melted, add Rice Krispies and M&M's.
Stir all together so everything is mixed and coated evenly (this should be done quickly so the dessert doesn't harden).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and level out by putting wax paper over the top and pressing firmly.
Let harden for awhile and cut into squares.
Makes 20 to 24 squares.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
When cool, add pineapple, bananas, nuts and strawberries.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set this in refrigerator to congeal (leave remainder at room temperature so it won't set).
After first half is set, spread sour cream over the surface.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Pour remainder of mixture over sour cream and let it set.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gently toss raspberries with mixture (don't break berries).
Pour into bottom crust; dot with butter.
Moisten edge of crust and top with remaining crust. Seal.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo and cracker crumbs in baking dish.
Mix crumbs with melted oleo and use mixture to top the casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until partially set. Fold in remaining ingredients and put in a 5-cup mold.
Chill until set.

title: quick stew
directions: Boil potatoes for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients & simmer for 15-20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a medium skillet, cook and stir sausage until no longer pink; drain well.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place dough in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes. Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, stir together the eggs, milk and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Carefully pour mixture into crust. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese atop.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 25 minutes, or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Grease a 10-inch angel cake tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Combine the whole wheat flour with sifted ingredients. Mix well.
Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl. Gradually beat in all the sugar.
Stir in oil.
Stir flour mixture into the egg mixture.
Add drained pineapple and grated carrots. Mix well.

Stir in chopped pecans and raisins. Turn mixture into the prepared angel cake tube pan and bake in a moderate oven (350°) 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly tapped with fingertip.
Cool on a wire rack for 15 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Into a bowl sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and then yeast mixture.
Stir until flour is dampened.
Knead on flour for a minute or two.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° about 12 to 15 minutes.
This dough may be stored in refrigerator.

title: salsa
directions: Boil vinegar to
reduce by half.
Chop or grind vegetables. Mix together
and
add to vinegar.	Bring to boil, then simmer for 1
hour.
Fill Mason jars to within 1/8-inch of top and add lid. Process
jars
in
water
bath
for
15 minutes. Makes 2 pints.

title: miss lillian's peanut brittle
directions: Combine the sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add the peanuts and cook until nuts become brittle and syrup turns amber.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Cook slowly to 300°, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add the baking soda; stir well, then pour onto buttered baking sheet. Cool and pull out until very thin.
Break into desired pieces. Makes 1 pound.

title: dinner rolls buttery sweet dough
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in warm milk, sugar, salt, butter, egg and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: deep chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt candy and syrup over boiling water in top of double boiler.
Add vanilla; set aside to cool.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate mixture and blend.
Sift soda and flour together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts.
Turn batter into large tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat until smooth, mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Fold in blueberries and bake in oven at 400 degrees about 25-30 minutes. Frozen or fresh blueberries can be used.

title: cream soups
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Add seasonings.
Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over low heat for approximately 30 minutes.

title: dumplings(for chicken)
directions: Roll out very thin, cut 1 1/2 inch squares.
Prick with fork. Drop
in boiling broth.
Simmer for 12 minutes.
Do not remove lid from pot until done, they will fall.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add carrots, oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Spoon into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Takes two. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until loaves test done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Cool completely.
If desired, can drizzle over with confectioners sugar.

title: easy crunchy top pound cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until smooth; add oil, flour, milk and flavoring.
Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a greased Bundt or tube pan.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with pineapple, green pepper, pecans, green onion and salt.
Pack in a crock and refrigerate. Serve with mixed crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set 3 to 5 minutes.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Stir ingredients together and chill.

title: crunchy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: thelma's pie
directions: Add lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir until thickened. Add nuts, cherries and whipping cream.
Fold in rest of mixture. Pour into a graham cracker or prepared crust.
Chill.

title: french fried onions
directions: Peel onions
and
slice 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with ice water and
let
stand
minutes.
Wipe
dry and separate in rings. Sift
together the dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add
the dry ingredients and mix well.
Dip onions in batter and fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: melt-in-the-mouth cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg and beat until light.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture and mix thoroughly, then stir in nuts.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set exactly 1 minute, then with broad spatula, pressing down firmly, quickly remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire racks.
Store airtight. Makes 8 dozen.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly; stir in hamburger seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Arrange cheese slices over mixture and top with uncooked biscuits.
Bake in 425° oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach stuffed flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make sure the nuts are finely chopped.
Put ingredients in the middle of flank trim steak.
Roll and tie flank steak on all sides in a good size frying pan.
Cook in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until you like it.
Cut in slices so stuffing is showing. Place on top of tomato sage demi glaze.

title: layered supper
directions: Divide potatoes between 2 (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch) baking dishes. Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange corn and green pepper over potatoes in each casserole.
Layer the onion then the carrots in each.
Crumble beef evenly over the vegetables.
Sprinkle with more salt and pepper.
Pat gently to smooth.
Top each casserole with tomato sauce.
Bake covered at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Makes 2 casseroles, 8 to 9 servings each.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients and 1 cup of pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Chill well before serving.

title: cheese cake(makes 2)
directions: Cream sugar, milk and cream cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crusts.
Top with pie filling.

title: kidney bean dip
directions: Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Mash beans into a smooth paste (I use a food processor).
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add beans and cook over medium-high heat about 5 minutes.
