Stir in seasonings.
Add reserved bean liquid to reach desired dipping consistency.
Stir in cheese and heat until cheese is melted. Serve warm with corn chips. Makes about 3 cups.
Reheats nicely in the microwave.

title: sarah's egg salad filling
directions: Stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Makes 2 cups or 6 sandwiches.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in flour 1 cup at a time.
Refrigerate dough for 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and roll dough out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut cookies with desired shaped cookie cutters.
Brush top of cookies with milk, then add colored sugar. Bake at 350° until done, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes in a large serving bowl until well blended.
Add hot potatoes and toss to coat.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef in skillet in butter until it loses its pinkness.
Transfer to a pot.
Peel and chop onions.
Saute until transparent.
Add to meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bouillon cube, minced garlic and seasonings.
Cook over medium low heat covered for 20 minutes.
For sauce, melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir to mix.
Add milk, stirring.
Cook for 3 minutes until thickened.
Add most of the cheese.
Let melt.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour half the sauce in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with lasagna, layering meat sauce and noodles.
Pour rest of sauce over top.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake 400° for 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook pudding and water until thick.
Add dry jello and cool. Add drained oranges, drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Can be made 1 to 2 days ahead and refrigerated.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots in slices; cook in salted water until almost done. Drain and cool.
Combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boiling point.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour over carrots and vegetables.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Keeps well for at least 10 days.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: birdie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Use with chicken, ribs and hamburgers.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sour cream and soup.
Grate cheese and stir in.
Mix in salt, pepper and hash browns.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, until brown and bubbly.
Half way through, stir the mixture.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until time to serve.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Meat Mixture:
Brown meat.
Season with salt, pepper, package of dry taco mix, taco sauce and beans.
Heat thoroughly.

title: champagne punch
directions: Core pineapple and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add sugar and bourbon.
Let sit at least 24 hours in airtight container.
Pour pineapple mixture into punch bowl.
Stir in champagne just before serving.
Add crushed ice as needed.

title: dill dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook onion and peppers in water for 2 minutes until tender. Mix remaining ingredients.
Add pepper and onion.
Spray casserole dish.
Top casserole with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.
161 calories; 3 grams fat.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook the onion in the butter until lightly browned. Blend in the flour. Add tomato juice and seasonings and heat to a boil. Lower heat and slowly stir in milk. Reheat to almost a boil. Serve with crackers.

title: coconut-caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown.
In bowl, combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk; beat until smooth and fold in whipped topping. Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in pastry shell, then 1/4 caramel and 1/4 coconut mixture.
Repeat and freeze pies.

title: bran muffins
directions: Blend until all ingredients are well moistened.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.

title: apple sheet dessert
directions: Combine.
Roll out 1/2 of dough and put in sheet cake pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine onions with garlic and rest of ingredients except tortillas, cheese and sour cream.
Bring sauce to a boil, reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes, covered.
Remove from heat.
Dip tortillas in sauce, add chicken strips to each, then roll tortillas and place in a casserole dish.
Continue until all tortillas have been used.
Add sour cream to remaining sauce and pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese over tortillas and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease	a
x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Spread nuts over bottom of
pan.
Mix
cake
mix as directed on package.
Pour cake mixture over pecans.
Mix cream cheese and margarine and add powdered sugar.
When well mixed, add coconut.
Mix.
Drop by spoonful
into cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Center of cake will shake when it is removed.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: *Save small amount of cheese to put on top of casserole.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain thoroughly.
Saute onion and celery in butter; blend in soup, milk, chestnuts (cut into two or three pieces), rice, broccoli and one-third of the jar of Cheez Whiz. Turn into a greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: sauce for fish and poultry
directions: Place pitted and peeled avocado in blender.
Add lemon, spices and garlic.
Blend until smooth.
Serve with fish or grilled chicken.
Serve immediately!

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Blend well in blender.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and butter, blend and shape to pie pan and chill.
Heat milk in double boiler, add marshmallows and stir until melted; cool thoroughly.
Combine whipped cream, creme de cacao, creme de menthe and green food coloring.
Fold into cooled marshmallow mixture.
Pour into chilled crust and chill until firm.
(May be made day ahead of serving.)
Serves 6.
Regular pie crust can be used.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: Put in top of double boiler and cook until thick and creamy. Continue to stir while cooking.

title: oreo freak-out
directions: Crush 12 Oreo cookies and place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer with softened ice cream, then caramel syrup, nuts and Cool Whip.
Top with 12 crushed Oreo cookies.
Freeze for 24 hours.

title: onions, by george
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until wilted and transparent.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Spread mixture in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Slice French bread in 1-inch slices.
Butter top of each slice and place on onion mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and bread is browned.

title: salsa
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Makes about 9 pints.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain excess grease, return meat to skillet and add other ingredients. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and continue to boil until it thickens.
This is wonderful on hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: no fat cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften dry yeast in 1 cup lukewarm skim milk.
Mix 1 1/3 cups flour and 2 egg whites in the yeast/milk mixture and beat for 100 strokes.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes.
Mix in salt and 1 2/3 cups flour.
Mix well until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spray casserole dish, pour mixture into dish. Bake at 425 degrees until done.

title: 7-up strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7-Up, cornstarch and sugar until thick.
Then add the 4 cups drained strawberries.
Pour into baked pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Blend together sugar and cheese; add flavoring and color as desired.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar. Press into candy mold.
Unmold at once.
If candy sticks, add more powdered sugar.

title: chocolate shot cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add vanilla, flour, soda and oats.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill dough in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Shape into rolls 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Coat each roll in chocolate shot.
Slice 3/8-inch thick and place on ungreased baking sheet, leaving space between slices.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: fresh cauliflower ham chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, simmer potatoes, water, onion and base covered 10 minutes.
Add cauliflowerets and cook 10 minutes more or until tender.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups milk, ham, nutmeg and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup milk with flour.
Stir into hot mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shoney's fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, cornstarch and sugar until thick.
Stir in jello. Let cool; then add fresh strawberries.
Put in baked pie shells and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: carrot meat balls
directions: In a large bowl mix beef, carrots, onions, egg, bread crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Heat oil in large skillet and brown meat balls.
Add gravy; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Unroll dough and press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with brown sugar.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add chopped nuts; blend and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in sugar.
When completely cool, roll again in sugar.

title: shrimp aspic salad
directions: Boil tomato juice.
Dissolve jellos in hot tomato juice.
Add catsup, Tabasco sauce, salt, vinegar and water.
Let partially set, then add 1 cup shrimp, stuffed green olives, chopped onion, ripe olives and celery.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini with remainder of ingredients.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: beer kielbasa
directions: Boil kielbasa in beer for 1 hour.
In saucepan, boil chili sauce and jelly until thick.
Cut kielbasa in 1/4-inch pieces. Add to sauce.
Heat to boil.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and cook until it pulls away from sides of the pan, about 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, cut off tops and add filling of pudding.
Makes 8 large or 12 small cream puffs.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top and pour 1 stick melted butter over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In very large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and eggs; stir well.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan for 40 minutes to 1 hour (depending on the thickness of pan).
Top with glaze of powdered sugar and water.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together and spread over brownies.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak squash in 3-quarts water with 2/3 cups salt for one hour. Pour off brine.
Make syrup of sugar, mustard seed, vinegar and celery seed.
Bring to a boil, drop in vegetables.
Bring to a boil again, but do not cook.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: italian freselle
directions: Combine
ingredients
and
mix	well.
Roll
into
long strips and cut into bite size pieces.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: low cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add liquid ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Add your favorite chocolate icing or eat without icing.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 10 ingredients at room temperature.
Do not "overbeat."
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Do not open oven door.

title: three bean coffee
directions: Mix coffee liqueur, tequila and hot coffee. Squeeze lemon and drop lemon into mug and mix. Top with cream and cherry. Serves 1.

title: chicken stir fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, chicken, ginger and red pepper in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons Crisco over high heat in a large skillet or wok.
Add chicken mixture. Stir fry until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Melt remaining tablespoon of shortening in skillet.
Add onions and carrots.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Add pea pods, mushrooms, red pepper and green onions.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry until heated through. Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6 (3/4 to 1 cup each).
Contains 131 to 175 calories per serving and 26 to 34 mg.
cholesterol.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook together the sugar, salt, cornstarch, Karo syrup and water.
Add strawberry jello and red food coloring.
Let stand until cool.
Gently coat strawberries with mixture and pour into prebaked pie shell.

title: swiss tuna grill sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, cheese, celery, onion, mayo, sour cream and pepper.
Spread filling on 8 bread slices.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Spread outside of sandwiches with butter.
Cook on hot griddle over medium heat about 3 minutes on each side (until filling is heated through and both sides are toasted).

title: dill muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 miniature muffin cups.
Blend all ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Arrange onions on top.
Spread undiluted soup on onions.
Sprinkle peas over soup.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: lori's lasagna
directions: Combine and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles. Layer in large flat casserole.
Spread 1 pound Ricotta or dry curd cottage cheese on top.
Spoon sauce over.
Layer crosswise more noodles.
Spoon sauce over.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese (1 pound divided for 3 rows).
Repeat twice more alternating directions of noodles.
Top with Parmesan cheese over Mozzarella and sauce.
Bake until warmed through at 350°.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put diced onions and chopped water chestnuts in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cook the rice per package instructions, then mix in casserole dish with the lemon juice, onions and water chestnuts.
If broccoli florets are too large, chop them into smaller pieces, then mix with other ingredients in casserole dish.
Mix about half of the cheeses, then the soups. Mix thoroughly, then add the last of the cheeses and mix again. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered.
Remove from oven and cover. Serves 8.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, then add in remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and lightly floured cake pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: "congo bars"
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.
Do not overcook (use 10 x 13-inch pan).

title: tomato raspberry jam
directions: Simmer tomatoes 10 minutes.
Add sugar and cook ten minutes. Add the jello and stir to dissolve.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
It's great!

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease a 7 1/2-inch round skillet with margarine.
Sprinkle with meal.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: la alicia mexican rice
directions: Combine water, chopped pepper, onions, let simmer until tender.
Put rice let simmer not boil until rice is tender.
Add other ingredients (large amount).

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, egg, onion and bread crumbs in a bowl; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Brown on all sides in hot oil in a large skillet.
Place balls in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour off fat except for 3 tablespoons. Blend flour into reserved fat in skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar and basil.
Stir well.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
Pour over meatballs in a casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease tins.
Sprinkle bottom of each tin with 1/2 teaspoon pecans.
Cream together butter and sugars. Add beaten egg yolks until blended.
Mix flour and baking powder. Add gradually to butter.
Beat egg whites.
Add cherry juice and fold in egg whites.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend vinegar and egg in cold water.
Mix with flour, sugar (salt) and Crisco.
Chill one hour in refrigerator.
Roll dough to desired thickness.

title: savory beef 'n beans
directions: In large heated skillet, cook and stir beef, onion, carrots and celery until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato paste, molasses, mustard and salt.
Bring to boiling; stir in beans.
Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Dissolve the soda in the milk.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake about 1 hour or until done.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Pour off grease.
Combine remaining ingredients and add hamburg and onion to bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat for 5 or 10 minutes.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add whipping cream.
Bake at 300° in tube or long pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check at 1 hour.

title: old south sausage stuffing
directions: Day Before:
Saute onions, green pepper and celery in melted butter until tender.
Remove from pan and reserve.
In same butter, brown sausage.
Refrigerate sauce and vegetables.
Next day, combine all ingredients and heat.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Mix soup and water.
Add 1 cup noodles, tuna, celery and onion.
Toss lightly.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
If too stiff, add a few drops of water.
Roll into balls.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375° to 400° or until brown.
May freeze unbaked balls and bake later.
Keep in airtight container after baking.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook in saucepan on top of stove until mixture thickens.
Add butter and raisins; continue cooking until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: marbles(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Have ungreased cookie sheet(s) ready.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
In large bowl, mix sugars with mixer.
Add butter and beat just until blended.
With mixer on medium, add egg, sour cream and vanilla; beat until pale and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Add flour mixture at low speed until blended.
Do not overmix.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler, stirring, until smooth.
Cool chocolate a few minutes; pour over cookie batter.
Use a wooden spoon or rubber spatula, fold chocolate into dough; don't mix completely.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet (s).
Bake 23 to 25 minutes.
Do not let brown.
Immediately transfer cookies with a broad spatula to a cool flat surface.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add blended margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer the mixtures in a pan: Oreos, filling, Oreos, etc.
Refrigerate until set.

title: bacon and cheese appetizer
directions: Spread on bread and slice in thirds.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: halloween treats
directions: Heat sugar and milk together in a 2-quart saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Then add vanilla and crackers. Mix well.
Cool, then form into 1-inch balls.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Poppy seed can be ground in a coffee grinder.
Add the hot milk and let soak overnight.
Next day, cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in poppy seed-milk mixture.
Sift dry ingredients: flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with the milk.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour in pie shell and bake at 325 degree until done.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: texas style cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in	large
bowl.
Pour
into
a hot greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese filo rolls
directions: Divide each chicken breast in half.
Pound thin between sheets of waxed paper.
Rub chicken with garlic and lemon.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper.
Center a slice of cheese and ham (optional)
on each portion and roll up neatly.
Line a cookie sheet with foil,
brush with melted butter and set aside.
Unwrap filo and cover with waxed paper and damp towel.
Brush a filo sheet with melted butter.
Top with second sheet and brush with butter.
Wrap chicken roll in filo and brush with butter. Continue with all rolls.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: "tommy's favorite"
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Mash and add butter, salt, pepper and French onion dip.
Mix well.

title: cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff in peaks.
Beat in sugar slowly.
Fold in slowly the saltine crackers.
Add walnuts.
Spread into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
When totally cool, spread Cool Whip on top and drop cherry pie filling on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate cake and serve after it sets.
(Best if made the night before serving.)

title: anna's broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Be sure to drain broccoli well.
In another pan, (I prefer an iron skillet) saute the chopped onion in the stick margarine, then add cheese and mushroom soup.
Mix all together and pour into casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or do as I do and bake in microwave for 20 minutes on High.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown meat, then put all together in a slow cooker on high until all cheese is melted (about 1 hour).

title: chocolate chip cookie dessert
directions: Slice one roll of cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream sugar, cream cheese and eggs; pour over sliced cookies.
Slice other roll of cookies over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tasty spread
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool.
In a blender, put the tomato, mustard, cream cheese and celery salt.
Cover and process until smooth.
Add the almonds and crumbled bacon and process 10 seconds.
Serve with Ritz or saltine crackers.
Makes about 1 cup of spread.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix eggs, vanilla, oil and sugar in a separate bowl.
Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Put in greased baking pan; bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian tropic
directions: Finely crush graham crackers.
Add melted margarine and sugar. Blend well.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Reserve a small amount of crumbs for garnish.
Slice bananas enough to cover crust.
Mix milk with lemon juice; pour over bananas.
Spread well drained pineapple over mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rhubarb in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In small bowl combine sugar, flour and cinnamon and sprinkle over fruit.

title: brown sugar cupcakes
directions: Mix all together.
Fill cupcake pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana split torte
directions: Cut Twinkies in half and put in dish with cream side up. Place crushed pineapple over Twinkies.
Put banana slices in pineapple juice until ready to use.
Make chocolate pudding as directed.
Take bananas out of juice and drain well.
Put on top of crushed pineapple.
Cover bananas with chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef into thin slices.
In 10-inch skillet, cook beef and garlic until beef is browned.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: spiced apple pork roast
directions: Remove and discard excess fat from roast. Slice slits in top of roast; insert garlic strips.

title: paprika chicken(paprika huner)
directions: Heat butter and saute onions until light brown.
Lay chicken pieces over onions and saute.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes.
When chicken is tender, remove and keep warm.

title: taco dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix salsa and cream cheese well.
Pour into flat dish and cover. Refrigerate at least 4 hours until set. Sprinkle with olives, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese before serving. Dip with chips.
To keep lettuce from browning, use a plastic knife to shred.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine chicken and 1/2 of the cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 1 1/2 tablespoons chicken mixture into wide end of each triangle.
Roll up from end to point.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour. Glaze while still hot.

title: sauteed crabmeat
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add crabmeat and sherry; heat thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: cheese apples
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix.
Add small chunks of cheese and mix well.
Place apples in quart casserole dish and spread cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seafood ragout
directions: If scallops are big, cut in half.
Heat butter in a 3-quart pan until melted.
Cook and stir in mushrooms, parsley and onion over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Heat to boiling and stir one minute; stir in fish, shrimp and scallops.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and sherry.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve on rice or pastry shells.

title: peppermint icebox dessert(serves 16)
directions: Fix graham cracker crust using 1 stick butter to 1 1/2 packages graham crackers. This will make 2 (9-inch) pie crusts. Whip 1 pint whipping cream with 1 teaspoon sugar.

Fold in 24 marshmallows, cut in 8 pieces each, 3/4 cup pecans and 1 1/2 cups crushed peppermint candy. Pour into the graham cracker crust; shave Hershey bars all over the top. This is to be kept in the freezer, covered with wax paper, until you serve it.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers; cut in slices.
Also slice the onions and sweet bell peppers.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour and drain.
Boil sugar and vinegar and spices until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumbers, onions and peppers; let boil 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: french beef au gratin
directions: In a large, heavy-bottomed pan, over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add onions; saute, stirring often, until caramelized, but not burned, 15 to 20 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove onions to medium bowl.
Add beef to pan; brown well on all sides. Return onion and any juices to pan.
In small bowl, mix flour, sugar, cumin, salt and pepper.
Add to pan; stir 1 minute, until bubbly.
Gradually add broth, stirring to scrape drippings from pan; simmer 10 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Place 1/2 cup fettuccine in each of 4 (about 16 ounce) ovenproof bowls; divide beef mixture over pasta.
In medium bowl, stir cheeses together; sprinkle over beef.
Broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute nuts in butter.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add remaining ingredients (including nuts) and churn.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12 or 13-inch long glass Pyrex dish.
Prepare cake mix as instructed on box.
Bake until done.
Then set aside until fairly cool.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into baked pie shell.
Chill and serve.
May use graham cracker crust.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and put on marshmallows which have been cut in half.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then drain marshmallows and add them plus the fruits to the cream which has been whipped stiff.
Allow to set for 1 hour.
Use as a dessert or put on lettuce leaf for a salad.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Spray a skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Brown the onions and beef in it. When browned, place beef and onions in the crock-pot. Add all other ingredients in a 5 or 6-quart crock-pot. Stir to mix thoroughly. Set heat setting to low, allowing stew to cook for 8 hours. Stir occasionally. Serve with corn muffins or Jiffy biscuits.

title: cube steak with mushroom and onion
directions: Brown steak on both sides in small amount of oil. Drain liquid from skillet. Chop onion and place on top of steaks along with mushrooms and their liquid. Add butter. Cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until tender.

title: cream puffs
directions: Beat until thick the heavy cream.
Add vanilla pudding and slowly add milk while beating the mixture.

title: jalapeno cheese and onion bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: In mixer, place water, honey and yeast.
Let yeast soften. Add at once all the rest of the dry ingredients, making sure salt is mixed into flour before adding to yeast mixture.
(Use dough hook on mixer.)
Add jalapeno and onion.
Continue to mix for 10 minutes on medium speed or knead by hand until it becomes elastic in consistency.

title: mexican cornbread ii
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients well. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all wet and dry ingredients together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: honey-celery seed salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients but salad oil in small bowl.
With mixer on low speed, add salad oil.
Store in refrigerator; serve with fruit salads.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Boil 1 minute (no longer).
Serve over ice cream or white cake.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and set aside for ten minutes.
Cream sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients, oats and half of chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Top with remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May be topped with whipped topping.

title: shreveport pepper steak
directions: Brown meat on all sides.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, ginger and sugar.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove meat. Add soy sauce, green peppers, bean sprouts and onion.
Cook, covered for 5 minutes.
Move food away from center of skillet; add tomatoes and cook, covered, 5 minutes longer.
Make a smooth paste of cornstarch and water.
Add to hot mixture.
Stir gently and cook until thickened.
Stir in meat and serve with rice.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: rotel chicken
directions: In oleo saute green pepper, onion and celery.
Add mushrooms, drained.
Boil chicken or chicken breasts.
Melt cubed Velveeta and add undrained Ro-Tel.
Combine vegetables, cheese and cooked spaghetti.
Mix in chopped chicken and LeSueur peas.
Mix and bake, covered 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead.

title: pot of gold salad
directions: Chop lettuce and mix with celery and shallots.
Add orange slices and almonds.
Mix remaining ingredients to make dressing. Toss dressing with salad.

title: hopping john
directions: Wash and sort the peas. In a medium saucepan, combine the peas and 4 cups water and bring to boiling. Reduce the heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes. Drain the peas, reserving the liquid. Set both the peas and liquid aside. In a Dutch oven, saut the onion in the bacon drippings until golden. Add water to the reserved liquid to make 4 cups. Add the water, peas, rice, salt and pepper to the onions and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat; cover and simmer for about 35 to 40 minutes until the peas and rice are tender and the liquid is absorbed. Crumble the bacon and stir into the Hopping John. Makes 8 servings.

title: texas gold bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine. Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla, mixing until thick.
Add zucchini and stir thoroughly.
Sift salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and flour.
Add to the first mixture and stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake in tube cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: Drain fruits and mix juice with water to have 3 1/2 cups liquid. Heat juice and stir in gelatin to dissolve. Mix fruits with gelatin in a 9 x 13 glass dish and congeal until solid.

title: dinner-in-a-pumpkin
directions: Combine beef mixture, soy sauce, brown sugar, mushrooms, soup and cooked rice.
Place all into hollowed out pumpkin.
Replace pumpkin top and oil all of pumpkin with cooking oil.
Place on cooking sheet; bake 2 hours at 325°.
Place pumpkin in center of table; serve your guests.

title: chicken with a difference
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, skin side up, in a single layer (or skin if you prefer).
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Baste with juice every 10 to 15 minutes. Bake chicken until well browned and tender (approximately 1 1/4 hours) at 350°.

title: rosamarina
directions: Cook noodles.
Don't overcook.
Set aside.
Drain fruit; save juice.
Mix juices, sugar, flour and salt into beaten eggs.
Cook until thick.
Pour over noodles.
Set in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Add fruit and Cool Whip garnished with cherries and serve.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat together eggs, pumpkin and oil, then add dry ingredients. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into tube pan or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until tests done.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing (recipe follows).

title: fruity fun salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, fruit and sour cream.
Refrigerate several hours.
Sprinkle coconut just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple quiche
directions: Mix spinach, eggs, milk, onion, mushrooms, sausage and cheese. Pour into crust and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: best ever broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice and drain.
Saute celery and onions in butter.
Put broccoli, rice, celery and onions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together 1 can cream of mushroom soup, milk, eggs and Miracle Whip.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Top with Ritz crackers, crushed and rolled in butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese and fruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water, then dissolve in hot milk with salt. Add cottage cheese, sieved.
Pour into ring mold and chill until set.
Serve on lettuce and surround with fruit.
Place bowl of mayonnaise in center of ring.

title: inside-out stuffed chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine stuffing mix and melted butter or margarine; toss well.
In a medium bowl, stir together soup and milk.
Dip chicken into soup mixture and then into stuffing, pressing with hands to coat.
Place on an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: olive curry rounds
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Slice French rolls thin (if using) and allow to dry overnight.
Turn over and spread.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
To freeze after spreading, freeze on cookie sheets, then store in freezer bags.
If frozen, bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Batter will be stiff. Roll dough into walnut size balls. Place on lightly greased sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 6-8 min. or till lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack. Cookies will be crumbly until cooled. About 2 dozen.
